1004032.Content: Probably only the last team left!

1004050.Content: Golem Source has dropped onto the platform... The patrol is keeping watch over it...

1004051.Content: We need to <style="emph-gn">get through this corridor and return to the platform</style> to destroy the Source. Watch out-it'll be chasing us the whole way!

1004052.Content: Damn, the Golem's moving-it's trying to repair its Source... We need to move faster!

1004053.Content: Adventurers, this wind tunnel will take you straight back to the platform!

1004054.Content: Unbelievable... even with that broken body, it can still attack! The turret's been destroyed! Even the patrol...

1004055.Content: The Golem's left hand has been destroyed!

1004056.Content: The Golem's right arm has been destroyed!

1004057.Content: The Golem's legs have been destroyed!

1004062.Content: Turret ammunition refilled! Now it can be used!

1004063.Content: Please proceed to other part platforms to provide support!

1004064.Content: I knew you can do it. Now go-<style="emph-gn">head to other platforms and provide support</style>!

1004065.Content: Thanks! The nuclear threat is neutralized. Go help <style="emph-gn">take out the other parts</style>!

1004069.Content: Head down. The nuke has been aborted!

1004071.Content: That Source is the core. Hurry, destroy it!

1004072.Content: What a tough bastard... Watch out for <style="emph-gn">the Giant Golem's attacks</style>!

1004073.Content: Suicide troops have appeared in the core area, please clear them quickly!

1004074.Content: Success! We beat it! Victory belongs to Asterleeds!

1004076.Content: Reinforcements are finally here... Allies... We've suffered heavy casualties.

1004077.Content: It's those gunners.. They've got the ammo. We have to <style="emph-gn">take it back if we want to activate the turret</style>!

1004078.Content: Turret ammo fully loaded! Quick, <style="emph-gn">use it</style> to destroy the Golem's right arm!

1004079.Content: It's the leader of the elite spearman squad. Adventurers, stay alert!

1004080.Content: The small turret's ammunition is depleted!

1004081.Content: Spearmen's leader is overpowered... Go support our allies, hurry!

1004082.Content: Thank heavens, the adventurers are finally here...

1004083.Content: The Golem is trying to launch a nuke-aim for its head to stop it!

1004084.Content: Adventurers, you must <style="emph-gn">recover the ammo and activate the turret</style>!

1004087.Content: Damn it, <style="emph-gn">the Gunners</style> have noticed us too!

1004088.Content: More enemies are coming-hold on a little longer! Just <style="emph-gn">one more hit</style> to completely destroy its nuclear system!

1004200.Content: Today! We will face that giant threat from Byrnhald! Should it cross this canyon, Asterleeds will be erased from history for good.

1004201.Content: Whether the future buries the ruins in dust or ignites the sky with fire, the gears of fate begin to turn here.

1004202.Content: So pull yourself together! We'll <style="emph-gn">split into three groups</style>, defeat the Byrnhald forces, and <style="emph-gn">reclaim the ammunition</style>!

1004203.Content: Then <style="emph-gn">power up the cannon</style>—and blast that big guy right in the face!

1004204.Content: I know it's tough, but with the help of the adventurers, we can definitely do this!

1004205.Content: Whatever the outcome, I am proud of you! Asterleeds is proud of you all!

1004301.Content: Ee-chan wants to be a director, so... here goes!

1004302.Content: Everyone, you're all my loveliest actors!

1004303.Content: Come find me when you're ready. Be sure to follow my script closely!

1004304.Content: On a sun-drenched afternoon, the clever Dorothy conceived a spark of inspiration.

1004305.Content: "Hey everyone-just thinking about the Seabreeze Festival in Asterleeds has me fired up! I've been mulling over it day and night... maybe it's time our Guild throws a party of its own. "

1004306.Content: "Thanks so much for all your support so far. Now we've got some work to do to pull this off-

1004307.Content: and I'll need everyone's help to make it happen!" Seeing the eager expressions on his companions' faces, Dorothy declared with joyful determination.

1004308.Content: Dress up as an <style="emph-gn">artisan</style> and take a seat <style="emph-gn">near Dorothy</style>.

1004309.Content: The artisans journeyed across rugged mountains and winding valleys to reach the Misty Cloud Mountain, where clouds drifted like a dream-tangible yet elusive.

1004310.Content: Some clouds held firm beneath their feet, while others vanished at a touch. As the group gazed at the White Cloud Dewdrop ahead, uncertainty shadowed their faces.

1004311.Content: Alright, time to see if these clouds hold up or disappear beneath me! Don't worry about me. I've got a bunch of leaves ready to cushion the plunge. "

1004312.Content: "Then I'm coming too!" "Count me in!" With those words, the tension lifted, and their thrilling descent into the white clouds began.

1004313.Content: <style="emph-gn">Harvest the White Cloud Dewdrop on the other side!</style>

1004314.Content: The Eastern Sea churned with fury, tornadoes twisted like voracious beasts, ready to consume everything in their wake.

1004315.Content: As Skyfish swarmed the skies like a tempest, the artisans calmly raised their woven baskets, prepared for this very moment.

1004316.Content: Undeterred by the danger, they pressed forward into the heart of the tempest.

1004317.Content: To their dismay, a savage wind suddenly whipped across the shore...

1004318.Content: Use the baskets<style="emph-gn"> to snatch fishes as they fell</style>.

1004319.Content: Every stone in the Thousand-Rock Dunes weighed as much as a fallen mountain.

1004320.Content: Even when working together, the artisans strong as oxen could only move them little by little.

1004321.Content: Yet now, they were all swept up in a shared conviction, their original purpose, a simple evening banquet, long forgotten.

1004322.Content: "Quick, push them this way!" Dorothy waved and called out from afar.

1004324.Content: The artisans gathered all the materials, and Dorothy finalized the preparations.

1004325.Content: The preparation lasted three days and nights. At last, the joy of success painted across every face.

1004326.Content: Under the spotlight, everyone danced with passion.

1004327.Content: Beside them, the bonfire blazed-like the hearts of the artisans, always burning.

1004329.Content: Cut! Thank you for your hard work-preparations for the next scene are underway.

1004330.Content: Such heartfelt, touching stories from the artisans... I was moved to tears.

1004332.Content: Hee hee. This stage play ends perfectly. Thank you all for your cooperation.

1004333.Content: "First things first, we've gotta brew the White Dew Wine. The key ingredient is <style="emph-gn">White Cloud Dewdrop</style>, and you can only find them in the heart of Misty Cloud Mountain of Asterleeds. "

1004334.Content: "Next up, the tornadoes've been tossing swarms of Skyfish onto the shore lately in Eastern Sea. And rumor has it, if you manage to <style="emph-gn">catch one mid-air</style> and eat it, you're set with good luck!" "

1004335.Content: "Third on the list, the Thousand-Rock Dunes are packed with all kinds of rocks. <style="emph-gn">Bring some back</style>, and I'll turn them into glowing orbs. "

1004336.Content: "Once everything's wrapped up, I'll go all out to prepare a feast you'll never forget, thanks again, everyone! " Dorothy gave a slight bow as he closed the meeting. Thus, the artisans' passion was set ablaze.

1004337.Content: If you're all ready, come to me for makeup!

1101001.Content:
Captain Jayden believes that the passage to leave here is behind the door, hopefully so. To be honest, I don't know if it's his intuition as a reconnaissance captain or if he's just trying to comfort our despair.
However, the key to open the door is on those terrifying giant machines, defeating them is impossible. Captain Jayden plans to send a small team to lure them to the door, and once the door opens automatically, lure them away so the rest can escape...
But this also means that the team responsible for luring the machines will never be able to leave.
I don't know why I still raised my hand voluntarily, is it because I am the oldest team member? Or have I already given up? Damn it, I can't help but feel scared at a time like this...

1301003.Content: Hmph, insignificant insects... Warriors who have pledged to the Dark Mist Legion-obey my command, destroy them!

1301004.Content:

Asterleeds' puppets, doomed to perish in the Void Mist-

1301005.Content: The one destined for destruction is YOU-!!

1301006.Content: Careful, Void Mist is getting thicker... Once it reaches a certain density, it'll start affecting your mind!

1301007.Content: Perish along with the Void Mist!!

1301011.Content: We must prevent him from releasing more Void Mist. Otherwise everyone will be eternally trapped here...

1301013.Content: (The entire Dark Mist Fortress lies engulfed in Void Mist. The air is thick with the rancid stench of decay and foreboding.)

1301015.Content: This time we must stop him...

1301020.Content: Denvel shattered the Imagine Seed and fled. This energy-it's coming from inside the Seed.

1301021.Content: I saw some other orbs of energy flying off too...

1301030.Content: Please, Commander Denvel, stop fighting. This war is pointless. Take everyone home...

1301031.Content: We can only go back if we emerge victorious-don't falter now! Stay strong!

1301051.Content: This device might be useful. Can you get it working, partner?

1301060.Content: We lost. The Dark Mist Legion... actually lost...

1301061.Content: No... This cannot be... I refuse to accept this-!!

1301062.Content: (This appears to be Denvel's memory from his defeat in the Asterleeds Independence War. As I observe this memory, the Engram contained within the fragment flows into my body.)

1301081.Content: (I should quickly find the exit and stay away from them.)

1301082.Content: (Let's look for an exit leading to the lower level ahead.)

1301083.Content: (An Anti-Gravity Ring! This looks like the path to get down there.)

1301084.Content: (The Void Engram accumulated within my body was purged by the energy of the Anti-Gravity Ring.)

1301091.Content: Of course I'm fine! This guy is just so annoying. Come on, <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, let's knock him out together!

1301092.Content: Hmph-I won't allow you to disturb Lord Denvel!

1301110.Content: (It's the energy from the Imagine Seed.)

1301123.Content: Partner, use the Imagine Seed to cleanse the Void Mist from your body now!

1301130.Content: I've got nothing more to teach you. You've already surpassed me.

1301131.Content: Master, don't sell yourself short. If this were a battlefield... I'd stand no chance against you.

1301132.Content: We'll never meet in combat—unless I betray my beliefs.

1301133.Content: (Is this a glimpse into the past of Tatta and Denvel?)

1301140.Content: (The legacy device ahead might be of some help...)

1301141.Content: (Looks like a gravity legacy-it can dispel the surrounding and lingering Void Corruption!)

1301150.Content: (What a magnificent gravity device... So this is the great Bapharian Legacy)

1301160.Content: (The gravity field here is distorted by that Legacy. It's as if I'm trapped inside a massive Anti-Gravity Ring...)

1301170.Content: (This Anti-Gravity Ring appears ruined, but it still managed to clear the Void Mist obstruction.)

1301180.Content: (Engram is still insufficient. Need to search for other Imagine Seed fragments.)

1301190.Content: The path is open. Partner, let's move.

1301191.Content: Let's go. End this, once and for all.

1301200.Content: (Airona went to find Hruga's Horn... Where could she be...?)

Stay away from the black fog, don't...


(Distorted handwriting) Glory to the Dark Mist Legion! Long live Lord Denvel!


Help me... Something is taking over this body...

1302002.Content:
June ▇▇, Year 600, Alician calendar
I was sent again today to reinforce the east-side Anti-Gravity Ring. Denvel calls these devices the "dawn of a new era," but every time I get near them, I feel uneasy.
... With our current status, are we really still qualified to use these Divine Legacies? What are Legacies made of, anyway? Are they sacred or defiled? Who can say?

At lunch, old Cole from the mess said three new recruits from the northern barracks went missing last night. The patrol found their dog tags with black mist lingering on them...

1331101.Content: Today marks the end of Asterleeds!

1331103.Content: The end has come. Cease your futile resistance!

1331104.Content: Just crumble into dirt, you pathetic insects!

1331105.Content: Look at you, faces twisted in struggle... How pathetic.

1331106.Content: Witness now-the power of the Void Mist!

1331107.Content: You cannot stop oblivion-not with such pitiful strength.

1331108.Content: Heh... The Dark Mist Legion's grand design culminates this day...

1331109.Content: This feeling... Lord. Are you calling me?

1331110.Content: Denvel, The pledge of power made unto thee shall now be honored...

1331111.Content: Perish with the Void Mist, you wretched worms!

1331112.Content: Still struggling? What a pitiful farce!

1331113.Content: Mere humans dare to defy me?

1331114.Content: Hmph... So the time draws near. No matter-all of this is merely the beginning...

1331115.Content: Shut up! These accursed voices again... I won't be chained by you ever again!

1331116.Content:
The future...?
I shed that illusion long ago!

But sadly... I no longer have the strength to escape.

2000012.Content: If anyone finds this note... please, bring this message to the outside world. The truth behind this war is ■■■■■■.

2000019.Content: There's no response at all... Maybe the red glow means this device is unusable.

2000024.Content: After activating the device, several energy-formed platforms appeared... Maybe I can use them to reach new areas and continue exploring.

2000025.Content: Unauthorized intruder detected. Defense mode is activating.

2000026.Content: The ■■ concentration in ■■ the Giant Tower is extremely high. ■■■■ Imagination Seed ■■■■■■

2000027.Content: No, this platform is very <style="emph-gn">unstable</style>... It feels like it's about to disappear- I need to get out of here quickly!

2000029.Content: These strange switches are arranged like a puzzle, as if inviting me to solve it.

2000030.Content: The sequence is incorrect... I need to switch to the Imagine realm first, then activate the main control device and observe carefully.

2000032.Content: Success! But the main control device still can't be used... Maybe I need to try again.

2000033.Content: Looks like to unlock the main control device, I need to figure out the activation sequence of these switches. Time to head back to the Imagine realm and take another look.

2000036.Content: The way these boxes are arranged seems way too deliberate... Could this be the key to unlocking something?

2000038.Content: The puzzle has been solved, and the chest is unlocked... Hurry over and check it out!

2000039.Content: The chest is sealed by some kind of energy. It probably needs a special method to unlock it.

2000041.Content: The stack of boxes in the center of the room might be connected to the scattered boxes around it. They could be the key to solving the puzzle.

2000042.Content: This chest isn't in its original position. Maybe in the past, it was where it's supposed to be?

2000043.Content: The chest's position doesn't match up. I might need to look for clues in other places to find a way forward.

2000044.Content: There are four switches in total, but only two are activated. Activating all of them should unlock the chest...

2000045.Content: The two switches adjacent to this one have changed color.

2000047.Content: The higher section of the box rotated 90 degrees clockwise.

2000048.Content: The lower section of the box rotated 90 degrees clockwise.

2000050.Content: I may not have survived... but I managed to take down a major threat. In a way, that makes it worthwhile. Ahem...

2000051.Content: At last, we've managed to lure those troublesome intruders here. We must Sigil this place immediately-to ensure the others can advance unhindered.

2000052.Content: God... why have You abandoned us?

2000053.Content: There's no exit ahead! Something dangerous lurks there-fall back now!

2000054.Content: Heh... where would we even retreat to? From the very beginning, our fate was already sealed.

2000075.Content: The sheer menace of the machinery is undeniable. Thankfully, many remain dormant, for if they had been fully operational, our existence would have been erased in an instant...

2000076.Content: A ring, dulled with age, bears an inscription within-"My Beloved■■." A relic, no doubt, left behind by a soldier of the reconnaissance team.

2000077.Content: It's a piece of standard equipment of the Dark Mist Legion, the damage so extensive that one can only imagine the ferocity of the battle it endured.

2000078.Content: The Divine's ■■ Pillar, a conduit of ■■■ energy for ■■■, destroy Golem■■■■ energy core. Open the gate to ■■■

2000080.Content: A red badge... The insignia etched upon it is unmistakable-the emblem of the Dark Mist Legion, from back in the day.

2000085.Content: An old, yellowish piece of graffiti. It's been pried open and closed countless times. The faint yet discernible brushstrokes exhibit a childlike quality, depicting a family of three and their companion, enjoyed their outdoor activities.

2000087.Content:
A slightly torn, unopened letter. The recipient's address reads: No. ■■, ■■ Street...
The letter was never delivered.

2000108.Content: The Baphariann Golem lies crumpled-battered with wear, as if it has long since lost any hope of functioning again.

2000109.Content:
And yet, these Golems-despite their dilapidated appearance-seem mostly intact. Upon closer inspection,
they only need minor repairs before they could be operational once more.

2000110.Content: Still... something feels off. An unshakable unease settles in my chest. As if these Golems aren't broken-but merely lying dormant.

2000111.Content:
They weren't completely destroyed. Was the recon team too eager to push forward? Or... did they simply stand no chance against...
? Regardless, we must proceed with caution.

2000112.Content: If a Golem of this quality ever reached the outside world-it would be hailed as a monumental discovery.

2000113.Content:
There's an overwhelming number of Golems here... This place must hold significant value to the Divine.
Could it be linked to that enormous pillar?

2000114.Content: So this... this is what the Golems look like when intact. At a glance, they were initially in a seemingly sealed state.

2000117.Content: I know the Council did what they thought was best, but...

2000118.Content:
I've done so much... and this is how they repay me?
No. I won't accept such betrayal!!!

2000121.Content: What's going on? The war ended years ago...

2000122.Content: The Andra Landing Battle... a memory long buried. A past soaked in sacrifice-one they'd rather forget.

2000123.Content: <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, be careful. The Byrnhalds are strong.

2000124.Content: Another Tina went to the front line. We need to catch up.

2000125.Content: This is the place! The Byrnhalds have broken through. Could it be...

2000127.Content: It's the Golem... No! <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, get out of the way!

2000129.Content: Great. You're safe... I thought I'd lost you.

2000131.Content: Don't give up! I'll save you.

2000132.Content: She hasn't realized... this isn't reality.

2000133.Content: Is anyone still alive? Please say something!

2000134.Content: It's my fault... I was too late!

2000135.Content: Please, if anyone's there, answer me!

2000136.Content: The Void Engram is becoming stronger.

2000137.Content: I can feel her... breaking apart...

2000138.Content: Did I... cause all of this? No-it wasn't me. It wasn't like that... No!

2000139.Content: None of this is real. Void Engram... it's affecting our minds.

2000140.Content: We waited for your rescue until the very end. It's all your fault.

2000141.Content: It's not my fault... please... don't do this...

2000142.Content: Wake up. No one ever blamed us!

2000143.Content: Please... don't do this to me...

2000144.Content: We can't stay trapped in the past. There are people waiting for us-in the future.

2000146.Content: I declare that Seal Watchers Tina shall submit unconditionally to the Council's oversight. Management protocols take effect immediately!

2000148.Content: Don't worry. I haven't disappeared. This is the only way to hold off Void Engram's Corruption.

2000149.Content: (So all of that... was Tina's memory?)

2000150.Content: (The wall... Let's <style="emph-gn">turn back</style> and look for another way out.)

2000154.Content: You have reached the deepest layer of Tina's consciousness. Mental energy can now be used to access different regions.

2000160.Content: Failed to protect Tina, the mental world is gradually resetting

2000161.Content: (The forest is burning... Where is Tina? Will she be here?)

2000164.Content: Wake up! Stop running from these memories!

2000165.Content: They ran... Something seemed to have fallen...

2000166.Content: (The figures of the surrounding councilors began to blur, even as their voices rang out with increasing clarity.)

2000167.Content: Please take your seat. The meeting is about to begin!

2000168.Content: (A door suddenly opened ahead. Where could it lead?)

2000169.Content: "I" have become completely lost in the Void Engram...

2000180.Content: (Let's look around first. There should be some clues related to Tina...)

2000181.Content: An old uniform. Seems to be Tina's uniform from her Asterleeds Defense Corps days.

2000183.Content:
(A bone and fang necklace- likely from an alien race. Burn marks can still be seen...
Was this left behind by Tina?)

2000184.Content: (This is the Seabreeze Medal awarded to Tina earlier!)

2000185.Content: (Might be important. Let's keep it for now. Finding them is the priority!)

2000187.Content:
July 13, Year 602, Alician calendar

Sigh... If I agree to their request, I'll never be able to leave Asterleeds again.
This is awful. It feels like I'm being treated like a criminal.
But if I refuse, it'll make things difficult for everyone...
What should I do?

Still, if this is the punishment the Kanamians have for me...
Then I don't mind being imprisoned forever.

...
I can't keep thinking about this.
If Olvera found out, she'd say I've lost it.

2000188.Content:
To: Warrior of the Sea Breeze, Tina
On behalf of Asterleeds, thank you for everything you've done for this city. You've always been our pride.
However, as a Seal Watcher, you bear the power and responsibility that concerns the peace of The Continent of Magna. I earnestly urge you to consider the requests put forth by the Council.
Lamond
February 7, Year 603, Alician calendar

2000189.Content:
Tina:
Latest update: The Creed members will also attend the hearing.
They're especially wary of your identity as a Seal Watcher and have already formed an alliance with the conservative faction of the Council.
Rest assured, the Council Chair and I are on your side, regardless of the outcome.
If you need anything, don't hesitate to reach out.
Olvera
July 19, Year 603, Alician calendar

3000029.Content: Look at what you've done. Is this what you wanted?

3000033.Content: Accept your fate. Struggle changes nothing.

3000034.Content: I do so love the way you fight against the inevitable.

3000035.Content: It's time to end it all.

3000038.Content: Hey, where do you think you're going? Don't wander off!

3000041.Content: Are you finished? Come-over here, now!

3010001.Content: Look, the sea looks great today!

3010003.Content:
File Number: S-23-06-A1

Report Time: Alician Calendar Year 600, June ■■■, 03:20

Reporter: Deputy Commander Jerrad

Urgency: Red Flag

At 02:10 today, The Bapharian Guard Post was attacked by the Dark Mist Legion.

The enemy took advantage of our unpreparedness and broke through the outer defenses, with an estimated force of about two hundred soldiers.

The combat strength of the Bapharian Guard Post is less than 30%, requesting higher-level support.

3010004.Content: These are the soldiers stationed here... What happened...

3010007.Content:
To {*me.name*}:

While investigating the village, I discovered some unusual phenomena. If you encounter them, be careful!

Crackling electric walls: Don't force your way through, you'll get electrocuted!
There's a crack in the wall. The electric power is weaker there.

Shiny monsters: More ferocious than before, they actively electrocute people!

These monsters drop electrified glowing objects. I call them lightning orbs.
Just carry those little balls, and the crack in the electric wall will become fragile, making it easy to break through. That's how I went inside and rescued everyone!

3010008.Content: (The further we go, the stronger the electric power...)

3010009.Content: (These monsters' electrics are getting stronger. Narulu should stay away.)

3010013.Content:
N-no, it's nothing.
Just calling your name makes me feel at ease.

3010014.Content: (Deprecated) (Although this child acts tough, he must be scared facing such danger...)

3010015.Content: (Deprecated) (I need to find a way to stop the lightning storm ASAP.)

3010016.Content: (Deprecated) There's a glowing orb up ahead!

3010017.Content: (Deprecated) That must be the Lightning Storm Core.

3010103.Content: Leave this place! The evil flames will consume us...!

3010104.Content: (What happened in the camp that drove the priests to flee?)

3010105.Content: (This appears to be a Dark Mist Legion weapons crate, but the weapons inside are extremely worn. Would anyone bring such deteriorated weapons into combat...?)

3010111.Content: It's the Dark Mist Legion! Airona and the others are in danger!

3010112.Content: Hold fast-Andra Resting Post is just ahead. Keep moving. Thank you...

3010113.Content: These pests never quit! We're counting on you to fight back once more,<style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>!

3010114.Content: It's a Dark Mist Legion's snare-watch your step!

3010118.Content: The priest must stay unharmed-guard him!

3010201.Content: Let him be for now. he's lost in his own thoughts. We'll speak with him once he's calm.

3010202.Content: How exactly are we going to do?

3010301.Content: They've all fallen into a deep sleep, Master. Why?

3010302.Content: Maybe the Void Engram drained their strength. We'll watch over them.

3020101.Content: Hum... so many monsters... so much lightning...

3020102.Content: Narulu, I can't hold out any longer...

3020105.Content: He stood his ground when others fled. We need hearts and talents like his.

3020106.Content: If it weren't for him, Minsterhorn would've fallen before we arrived.

3020107.Content: Corps needs young talent like him... to safeguard the future of Asterleeds and its people.

3020108.Content: Moreover, he witnessed Denvel wield the "Strength." That might be the key to tame these lightning storms...

3020110.Content: Who knows what dangers lie ahead... Stay sharp.

3020301.Content: But damn, Narulu... you actually got struck by lightning and walked it off?!

3020302.Content: You're solid in a crisis! I like that! Once this is over, you should join the Corps-Big Bro Jerrad's got your back!

3020304.Content: (Olvera was right-these s are highly active. There's something deeper here... I need to scout ahead and uncover the truth.)

3020305.Content: (The body that had collapsed from the earlier tremors across the plains now throbbed with pain once more.)

3020306.Content: (I can sense intense Void Engram from the mark... Perhaps Resonance can dispel it.)

3020310.Content: The Void Engram has completely lost control...

3020311.Content: I don't want to become a monster...

3020313.Content: I beg you, just let me go...

3020401.Content: Only one step remains. If we can achieve Engram Resonance, this chaos will finally be put to rest. All our hopes now rest upon you.

3020402.Content: The Strength flowing through the plants remains unstable. As long as the mark endures, so too will the chaos...

3020403.Content: Mr. Yasser? Ms. Agnes? Are you home?

3020404.Content: It's Narulu's cat. How can this be... Here is its home...

3020405.Content: The house is empty. Little one, can you show us where your humans are?

3020406.Content:
[Month X, Day X]
The war ended, but that person never came back. Mom and Dad didn't cry. They just took me out of the city and built this forest of memorial stones.
The Forest Keeper... If one guards the stones for a lifetime, can they see their loved ones' souls after death?

[Month X, Day X]
Sigh... I got caught trying to enlist in the Asterleeds Defense Corps. Mom kept crying... Dad just sighed. "You can't break your mother's heart again, Narulu. She already lost one child. She can't lose another. "
I'm sorry... I just wanted to become strong, strong enough to protect the people I care about.

[Month X, Day X]
No matter what I say, Mom and Dad won't let me join the Corps.
What should I do?

[Month X, Day X]
Today I visited the Pioneer Bureau and saw the adventurers on the leaderboard. They are so strong!
Maybe joining the military isn't the only path for me to become strong...

[Month X, Day X]
This time, Mom and Dad didn't object.
I'm going to become the strongest adventurer. I don't want to lose anyone ever again.
3020406.ChatName: A diary of an unknown owner

3020407.Content:
"To my stupid, forgetful little son,

I have left the door key for you—please take it. This is the last one, so I urge you to keep it safe. Should you lose it again, I'm afraid you will have to spend the night with the cats!"
3020407.ChatName: (A key with a small note attached)

3020408.Content:
{*me.name*}! I found the cause of the strange weather!

The Engram balance in the plains was suddenly disrupted, throwing the entire ecosystem into chaos.

(To put it in a metaphor: It's like someone flipped over the cooking table, and the sweet pudding turned into deadly spicy food.)

Theoretically, an Engram Core will manifest at the heart of the disaster. Destroying the core should bring an end to the chaos!

Note: The Engram Core will bind itself to the powerful monsters affected by the disaster. If you encounter one, you must tread carefully!

Airona, at the Statue of the Hero

3020501.Content: Hey, Narulu, are you all right? You look exhausted. Don't tell me that lightning scrambled your brain...

3020503.Content:
{*me.name*}:
There's something I should tell you.
Denvel once helped me during my time in the Knights. He guided me forward when I was lost. Without Denvel, I wouldn't be who I am today.
But now, he has become a villain. And I was given the job to take him down. Do I have to choose between gratitude and justice?
"If someone must be sacrificed for him to awaken and atone, then let it be me. " With that resolve, I prepared the Imagine Seed.
Once used, the Imagine Seed will affect both Denvel's mind and power. But I will lose Bio-Engram equal to the power.
If I use it too many times, my life will eventually be drained.
By the time you read this letter, I may already be gone.
I'm sorry for telling you everything this way. I hope my decision can help you all.
Please don't hesitate. Keep moving forward.
Your eternal ally, Tatta

3030101.Content: <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, thank you for being willing to help me.

3030103.Content: I know you've seen it. It belongs to the past. Let it rest.

3030104.Content: Denvel's glory is long gone. Now he's the Knights' disgrace and the indelible stain Byrnhald cannot erase.

3030105.Content: I swore to witness his fall myself, and your belief in me... is all I need.

3030106.Content: More enemies on the other flank. Tatta and me will draw them off. We will leave it to you to slip inside. Good luck, pal!

3030107.Content: It's Denvel... I have but one chance, I cannot afford to squander it...

3030108.Content:
Date: ■■,■■
"I stumbled across it by accident that day. The power Lord Denvel mentioned... it's real. Ever since, I've believed that as long as he's around, the Dark Mist Legion can't be stopped."

Date: ■■,■■
"That creep's been tailing us again. Just like a stray that refuses to be tamed. Honestly, wouldn't it be easier to just get rid of him?"

Date: ■■,■■
"All in. No holding back. Wipe it all out. I'll be the sharpest blade in the fight until Asterleeds falls."

3030109.Content:
Lunch: 300 Luno → Prices in Asterleeds are outrageous! Do I need to skip the dinner?

20 Luno couldn't even get me half a loaf of bread for dinner. In the end, I settled for a glass of water, stomach gnawing with hunger.

After purchasing that potent potion, I was completely broke.

I should've known better than to charter that run-down vessel... If I hadn't, I'd never have crossed paths with that con artist. When is that wretched old cheat going to return my deposit?

Right now, I'm very much close to asking {*me.name*} for a loan. Maybe the Pioneer Bureau has better salary...

But no. I've already burdened others far too many times. One must learn when to stop.

Hmm, I'll endure this. Just a little longer. Once everything is over, I swearCI'll return to Byrnhald and treat myself to roast chicken.

3030110.Content: The guards are on high alert. I'll chart a path...

3030111.Content: <style="emph-gn">Circle behind them. Hit the blind spot</style>. I'll regroup with you later.

3030112.Content: Tatta had spent every last coin on this potion, and it was worth every luno-powerful stuff...

3030113.Content: Two sentries are patrolling the perimeter. Wait for the gap... Go-quietly.

3030114.Content: That was close... No more slip-ups

3030115.Content: I've already caused enough tension. I can't afford to make Tina worry again.

3030116.Content: All is clear... Now, we find Denvel.

3030201.Content: The road ahead would only grow more treacherous...

3030203.Content: Another guard up ahead. Take him down quick!

3030204.Content: With this level of security, Denvel has to be nearby! We've come this far, so let's keep our spirits up and press on!

3030205.Content: No targets within range. Please move closer.

3030206.Content: It's you... that pesky little insect from Asterleeds.

3030208.Content: We have knocked them out! Now, for Denvel!

3030209.Content: It was close! Two more targets!

3040101.Content: With the plains in this state... Should we return to the city and seek Priest Allan's advice?

3040102.Content: Alack... when it comes down to it, these matters don't really concern the Creed. We're better off staying out of it.

3040201.Content: Will this path take us to the Engram?

3040202.Content: I can feel the Engram radiating from there.

3040203.Content: You can feel it? There's something mysterious about you.

3040204.Content: This area is filled with wartime pollutants. Extremely toxic! Are you sure we are heading the right direction?

3040205.Content: Is there a way around it?

3040206.Content: Of course there is! Follow me!

3040207.Content: (That priest-it's Stanley! What is he doing here of all places?)

3040208.Content: Looks like someone's over there. Let's check it out!

3040209.Content: This entry will take us deeper into the tunnel.

3040211.Content: (This should be enough. Use the collected Engrams to help the people who collapsed on the ground)

3061201.Content:
When moonlight kisses the tide's high crest, The ocean sighs in silken rest.
Blue silk drapes where lanterns rise, Like stars awakened in the skies-
Fireworks bloomed in the velvet night,
Echoes danced with the tide's delight.

A stranger sways on moonlit sand, With every step, a spell is planned.
Starlight weaves through midnight strands, A crown of stars by fate's own hand.
Her flowing sleeves caress the silver shore, Like whispers lost in ocean lore.
She smiles as fireflies light the air, A fleeting dream, too bright to bear.

Through Flame and Star, the tale takes flight, A dance of dawn, a blaze of night.
They stitch warm dreams in ocean's hue, With threads of gold and skies of blue.
A distant tune begins to start, It softly stirs within my heart:
"Lift the prologue, let fate unfurl, Begin the path that shapes your world."

Waves spun threads of foamy white,
Loosening knots where sky meets tide.

3061301.Content:
When the wind spirit danced and lifted her dress,
Its wings brushed the dawn in a sky-tinted mess.-
A beam of light cuts through the haze, Unraveling threads of silvered maze.
The Rudder Anemone turns face to sky, To greet the light as it drifts by.

The knight came bearing castle-baked treats,
While Senyu brought jam the villagers keep.
"Your eagle snatched my moonfruit prize!"
He points at the Blade wielder with an empty bowl with teasing eyes.

Ribbons ride the wandering breeze, Gliding soft through fields with ease.
A velvet green rolls far and wide, To meet the glow where dreams abide.
A shutter clicks, the stillness breaks, As roosting birds in silence wake.
Through ruins and peaks the sun descends, Its fiery glow where daylight ends.

Let the sea of clouds drift slow and wide, One final gloaming before they slide-
On these wide plains, among peaks cloud flows, An endless ukiyo-e quietly glows.
3061301.ChatName: The manuscript scattered by the wind

4000001.Content: "Warning: No trespassing by thieves or Olvera."

4000002.Content:
"Become an Adventurer and explore uncharted ruins! The Frontier Division needs you!"
-Pioneer Bureau, Garrison of Asterleeds

4000003.Content:
"During the Public Day, do not light Starsoul Lanterns inside homes or store to prevent fire hazards."
"Please follow the majority of citizens and proceed to the Statue of the Hero to release your Starsoul Lanterns."
-Joint Neighborhood Notice of Entertainment District

4000004.Content:
"How terrifying... Just what kind of monster could face Olvera head-on?!"
"That power... It's practically inhuman!"

4000005.Content:
"Rab: Mascot of Asterleeds"
"Honor the brave cat who warned Asterleeds Defense Corps during the Asterleeds Independence War."

4000006.Content:
"Report: Signs of Humanity organization activities have been detected within the Ruins of Andra City."
"Response: The ruins pose extreme danger, making long-term human survival highly unlikely. Maintain observation."

4000007.Content: "In memory of the Airies who brought fresh water to the front during the Asterleeds Independence War."

4000008.Content:
Correspondent 03:
Celestial Sigil energy conduits confirmed clear.
Ruins lockdown protocol fully executed. Giant Tower
Demolition Device-activated.

4000009.Content:
Dinner Before the Warship's Departure:
"The crew indulged in a hearty feast-bread crafted from the wheat of the West Byrnhald Peninsula,
spiced Caprahorn roasted crisp,
and steaming bowls of meat stew.
Everyone feasted in high spirits-all except Johnny, who sat brooding in silence.
That odd fellow... Had he not once dreamed of knighthood in his youth?
His chance is right before him now."

4000010.Content:
Johnny...
let me carry your dream forward-the dream of becoming a knight.

4000011.Content:
Johnny, I'm sorry.
Becoming a knight... it's no simple feat.
If I make it back to Byrnhald, I'll build you a monument with my own hands.
Wish me luck...

4000012.Content:
Soldiers of the Asterleeds Defense Corps,
ready the cannon! We must drive the invaders out of Byrnhald!

4000013.Content:
Let the thunder of our cannon echo across the plains!
The dignity of our citizens shall not be violated!

4000014.Content:
New recruits of Asterleeds Defense Corps, heed this warning:
stuffing stones into your cannon's muzzle doesn't make it deadlier-
it ruins your weapon.
Don't make me witness another fool's mistake.

4000015.Content:
New recruits of Asterleeds Defense Corps:
Shells ain't pillows.
Not all of us sleep like baby angels. Some of us chew steel for breakfast.

4000016.Content:
New recruits of Asterleeds Defense Corps:
Stop opening food jars by smashing them.
Step on broken glass,
and we'll drag your bloody stumps straight to the front lines.

4000017.Content:
Golem, Model 1:
Designed for the battle against dragons.

4000018.Content:
Golem:
It is inscribed with the emblems of the Bapharian Creed and Byrnhald.

4000019.Content:
[Officer] "Focus fire on their artillery! Take those Asterleeds down!"
[Soldier] "S-Sir! Massive Engram detected!"
[Officer] "What?! I need coordinates-NOW!"
[Soldier] "It's-it's coming from behind us-!!"
[Soldier] "ARGHHH-!"

4000020.Content: A spear tipped with sharpened animal bone

4000021.Content:
No tribesman is permitted to leave the village.
Disobedience to the Chieftain will be punished harshly.

4000022.Content:
To the young men of the tribe:
Trade with the Asterleeds is forbidden.
Unauthorized possession of Asterleeds-made goods is grounds for punishment.

5000001.Content: It's Rorola! We have to help her now!

5000002.Content: Careful. The space ahead is unstable. The elemental turbulence has crystallized into a Core.

5000003.Content: A... tornado...? Is this the Dark Mist Legion's doing?

5000004.Content: The Thunder Element here is unstable—likely a byproduct of the turbulence caused by the Core. Let's attempt resonance.

5000005.Content:
Rorola, wait for us!
Geez, she's too fast!

5000006.Content: We can't rush in blind. Let's first try to disperse the elemental turbulence around us.

5000007.Content: These ruins are full of danger. We need to catch up to her quickly.

5000008.Content: It appears the goblins release elemental energy when defeated.

5000009.Content: We should collect the energy before it fades.

5000010.Content: Look! There is another turbulence caused by the storm!

5000011.Content: Looks like the storm's to blame after all.

5000015.Content: As expected of you, <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>! It even looks like you have wings! Stay alert!

5000016.Content: (The wind currents are even more chaotic here...)

5000018.Content: The goblins' Anomalies must be caused by this chaotic Wind.

5000019.Content: Stay close. We still have work to do.

5000020.Content: (The wind's strong. If I fall, it won't end well. Better be careful.)

5000021.Content: (So many soldiers are down here... We must find Rorola!)

5000022.Content: (What intense winds! Maybe I can ride it to glide farther...)

5000023.Content: (Wait... that sound... fighting! Could it be Rorola?)

5000024.Content: Dark energy lies ahead. Be on your guard.

5000025.Content: This goblin is several times larger than normal. It must have been corrupted by dark energy.

5000026.Content: The only way forward is to take it down.

5000027.Content: Thank you! Please, help me find my father!

5000029.Content: (Is... that the Core of the turbulence? Maybe I can try resonating with it...)

5000030.Content: Be careful, <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>. I sense dark energy just ahead...

5000033.Content: (The winds are strong. We're almost there.)

5000036.Content: That voice... No! It can't be... Father!?

5000037.Content: (Oh no... I have to catch up with her!)

5000038.Content: The lift still works. Follow me.

5000040.Content: It's incredibly dangerous here, I almost lost my footing. I'll have to proceed with caution from now on.

5000041.Content: Guess I'll just have to jump down carefully... wheee!

5000045.Content: All the wounded Kanamians have been rescued

5000046.Content: The Thunder Element turbulence has been quelled

5000047.Content: The Dark Mist Legion has been defeated

5000049.Content: There's a lift here. Let's use the joystick to take it up.

5000050.Content: The Mutant's trying to escape-stop it!

5000051.Content: It's channeling Wind energy-break the Wind Shield!

5000052.Content: Henry drops wind energy. Breaking his Super Armor will release even more!

5000053.Content: Henry's hiding among these clones... Find the real one!

5000054.Content: High incoming DMG! Use your <style="emph-gn">Defense Skill</style>!

5000055.Content: Lure Boarrier King into <style="emph-gn">charging the pillar</style>!

5000090.Content: <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, look at those lightning particles. We might be able to harness them to dissolve the dark energy within this monster!

5000091.Content: Watch out! The wind energy in that monster is about to explode!

5000092.Content: The Core must be heading towards Igoreus. We need to go this way!

5000095.Content: It's down! Now's the time to strike!

5000096.Content: This is our moment! Finish it now!

5000098.Content: We've entered the eye of the storm. We need to figure out how to navigate through it.

5000099.Content: Rorola is up ahead, but so is the Dark Mist Legion... It's bad!

5000100.Content: Tina! Olvera! I knew you would find this place!

5000101.Content: Soldiers are here too... wonder if we'll run into them.

5000103.Content: Rorola and Chieftain, you must stay safe.

5000104.Content: Help me... I've been struck by lightning!

5000105.Content: Help me... I've been struck by lightning!

5000107.Content: A Soldier fell here. He looked like an officer.

5000109.Content: Those Kanamians won't lay a finger on our plans!

5000110.Content: Here is an undersized fallen Soldier.

5000111.Content: Damn it... I won't live to see our victory... But you... you must win

5000113.Content: Those Kanamians won't lay a finger on our plans!

5000114.Content: Damn goblins... I hope the Void Corruption swallows this whole damn place...

5000115.Content: War's cruel... I'm ready. Just... it hurts to leave it all behind.

5000116.Content: Ha... You think you're a hero? It's not as simple as it seems...

5000117.Content: A fallen Soldier lies ahead-his fate already sealed.

5000118.Content: A fallen Soldier lies ahead-his fate already sealed.

5000119.Content: None of this will end. My comrades will carry on my legacy.

5000120.Content: You think defeating me means victory? How naive...

5000121.Content: Watch closely... as long as we live in even a single heart, we will never fade.

5000122.Content: Nobody's stopping us... even if I...

5000123.Content: When I close my eyes, I see a world awaiting us... a world we will conquer.

5000124.Content: The wind... The elemental turbulence is tearing everything apart.

5000125.Content: These goblins... they've mutated. Even the Dark Mist Legion can't handle them.

5000127.Content: Look into my eyes... you will never understand the strength of our will.

5000128.Content: Strike me again. Make it quick.

5000129.Content: Slay me if you wish, but our creed will not perish with your sword.

5000130.Content: A light blow to the soldier's head

5000131.Content: These soldiers, temporarily unconscious, may have crucial information on them.

5000132.Content: It seems a fierce battle took place here...

5000133.Content: Scattered debris all over the place. Yet, nothing of immediate significance remains.

5007001.Content: This energy actually revived and strengthened it!

5016002.Content: It's Olvera! Warriors, now's your chance to act! Take her down!

5016003.Content: Olvera, you won't make it out of here alive!

5016004.Content: The warriors of the Dark Mist Legion... must never be allowed to fail!

5016005.Content: Drink...! My flesh and soul-I sacrifice it all to become the blade that cuts the enemy down!

5016006.Content: Ugh... Aaah...! Power... power's surging through me...!

5016012.Content: Waaah! I'm so sorry! What the hell was I even thinking?!

5017001.Content: So... there was a rat among us. No worries, I'll take care of it.

5017004.Content: You follow me! Let's get going!

5017006.Content: Void Engram is everywhere... There's no way through.

5017007.Content: Strange... he's gone? He couldn't have just vanished-<style="emph-gn">there must be a way in</style>!

5017008.Content: Found it! There's a way up!

5017009.Content: Damn it, there are still guards ahead. Let's scout around for another way in.

5017010.Content: An abandoned well here... Weird, the wooden cover looks loosely placed.

5017011.Content: Why are these two still standing?

5017012.Content: Hmm... who were they again? Oh right, the artisan's wife and kid.

5017013.Content: The artisan betrayed us-they have no place in this world anymore.

5017014.Content: Those mother and daughter locked in the cell over there... Their clothing suggests they're Asterleeds. We have to get them out.

5017016.Content: They're gone now-please, get me out of here!

5017017.Content: This whole place is swimming in Void Engram-watch your step, pal.

5017018.Content: Hey, that path over there looks clearer-let's check it out.

5017019.Content: This place... It's the Dark Mist Legion's prison hold. Denvel might've locked Tatta in here. Let's search the area.

5017020.Content: Tatta revealed that Denvel is ready to launch his plan to destroy Asterleeds-he begged us to let him out.

5017021.Content: Tina and I hid behind the barricade as Denvel and the Man in Black arrived, loudly plotting their final assault on Asterleeds

5017022.Content: Once Denvel was gone, we freed Tatta from the cell. Tatta led everyone out through a hidden escape route

5017023.Content: Oh no, Denvel's turning toward us!

5017024.Content: A Dominion duty is to achieve peace with the least amount of sacrifice.

5017025.Content: Spare me the sentiment! We could bring them down together!

5017026.Content: You're not the Denvel I once knew. I won't be a part of this!

5017028.Content: Now's our chance. Let's move somewhere else!

5017029.Content: Denvel's finally moved on... That was close.

5017031.Content: Hold on... something feels off over there.

5017032.Content: This place... it's a massive stretch of ruins. Find a way to get through.

5017033.Content: The cliff is steep-too steep to descend.

5017034.Content: We can't continue this way. We'll have to turn back and find another path

5017035.Content: <style="emph-gn">The entrance</style> may be nearby. Search the area for anything suspicious!

5017036.Content: Stay alert. Someone might be nearby.

5017037.Content: If you're no longer of use to me, then I'll deal with you-after I've finished with Asterleeds.

5018001.Content: That one's with the Dark Mist Legion! Seize him!

5018002.Content: For those we've lost-we won't let him escape!

5018003.Content: He looks dangerous... we might not stand a chance.

5018004.Content: Dangerous or not, we must stop him!

5018005.Content: There are more of us-together, we can take him down!

5018006.Content: (These people... they're unhinged. I need to get out of here-fast.)

5018007.Content: (No way forward... I'll have to find a nearby spot to jump from....)

5018008.Content: (Maybe if I reach a store, I can hide inside!)

5018010.Content: We've got him! Come over here!

5018012.Content: Damn it... they're closing in fast. There's no escape at this rate...

5018013.Content: (Damn it! I can't let them surround me.)

5018014.Content: (Here are so many people. I need to draw them away somehow!)

5018015.Content: There he is! Get more people-now!

5018017.Content: [Do not let the angry mob get close!]

5018020.Content: I admire your courage, but I wonder... does your strength truly match your boldness?

5018021.Content: Just a bit of sleight of hand.

5018022.Content: Far too soon to challenge me, I'm afraid. I am Quinin!

5018023.Content: Resisters! Today, you are witnesses to the revival of the ancient Kanamian Elite Trial!

5018024.Content: Necalli, the defiant beast who arbitrarily strayed from his ranks, and his fellow adventurers will now face...

5018025.Content: The embodiment of unrelenting might-seasoned adventurers from distant lands—the Storm Weaver!

5018026.Content: And the ruthless executioners who hunt the wicked without mercy—the Dark Twin Spirits!

5018027.Content: The time has come. Choose your opponent!

5018028.Content: Will you face the Storm Weaver, whose fury crashes like thunder? Or the Dark Twin Spirits, bearers of divine relics?

5018029.Content: First stage trial has come to a close!

5018030.Content: Without further ado, let us proceed to the second stage of the trial!

5018031.Content: Take a short rest if you must. Then return to me to select the next challenge.

5018032.Content: Ah, my favorite part... the Will Trial. It begins now!

5018033.Content: To lead the resisters, one must possess a will of iron!

5018034.Content: Necalli-though your strength has been sapped, your spirit as Kanamia Brave remains...

5018035.Content: Reclaiming your power should pose no obstacle.

5018036.Content: Now, to make this trial a bit more engaging, I hope you don't mind if I raise the stakes.

5018037.Content: The Divine Punishment Bird snatched their souls, dangling them from its perch. Clinging to the last shreds of Will, they reclaimed what was theirs.

5018038.Content: And now, the moment I've eagerly awaited... The Faith Trial begins!

5018039.Content: Never did I think you would pass my meticulously crafted trial... Very well. Proceed to the next trial.

5018040.Content: Feel the wrath of these Undead Monsters as they self-destruct!

5018041.Content: Let's spice things up a little more, shall we?

5018042.Content: Their demise shall take friend and foe alike!

5018043.Content: Let's spice things up a little more, shall we?

5018044.Content: Watch your step, outsiders. Here's a little jolt to keep you on your toes.

5018045.Content: Mind your allies. Don't go running headlong into your own team.

5018047.Content: Fight with all you've got! According to legend, the victor shall earn the ancestors' blessing!

5018048.Content: Face the might of my handpicked elite mercenaries!

5018052.Content: He is undefeated, unmatched in every battle! He is...

5018053.Content: Storm Weavers, beware! A loss here means the resisters will turn their backs on you.

5018054.Content: I'm afraid you don't have what it takes

5018057.Content: Ah... Seems the Storm Weaver are off their game today.

5018058.Content: Another binary choice awaits. Choose wisely!

5018059.Content: Choose incorrectly, and defeat is all but certain!

5018060.Content: Stand by Necalli and help him recover the scattered Engram.

5018061.Content: Your adventurer buddy can't protect you forever, Necalli...

5018062.Content: Some light trials-for those enduring the torment of this path.

5018063.Content: Congratulations. You've passed yet another test

5018064.Content: I must admit, your performance has exceeded my expectations.

5018065.Content: So I've prepared a little surprise for you...

5018066.Content: <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, Quinin's a slippery bastard-better watch your back.

5018067.Content: When you're ready, make your choice. I'm eager to see what you'll do.

5018068.Content: The Kanamian hunters will now strike at random-be on your guard!

5018070.Content: Capture the boarlets <style="emph-gn">when they are exhausted</style>

5018072.Content: Behold! The thundering rush of Boarlets from the Plains of Asterleeds!

5018073.Content: Defeat all four Boarlets in the allotted time, and you'll earn the bonus reward I've set aside!

5018074.Content: Well now! I have give it to them. The adventurer has more mettle than I expected!

5018075.Content: But enough leisure. The final trial looms!

5018077.Content: Fortune can only get you this far.

5018079.Content: I can feel my strength fading... Quinin, what have you done?!

5018080.Content: <style="emph-gn">Block</style> Stellar Engram Orbs, and focus fire to shatter Necalli's Shield!

5018081.Content: Behold the embodiment of unrelenting might—the Storm Weaver!

5018082.Content: I'm starting to feel almost sorry for you all

5018083.Content: Was this trial... truly so pathetic?

5018086.Content: Wonder if you'd have squeaked by had you picked a different trial...

5018087.Content: Trial terminated! Save your pointless struggling!

5018089.Content: So much for the leisure time...

5018091.Content: If you're prepared, come to me!

5018097.Content: Well done. Now we begin the next trial.

5018099.Content: And now, the final trial begins...

5018101.Content: A DoT field is forming. <style="emph-gn">Keep your distance from Allies and their souls!</style>

5018102.Content: Try this on for size-<style="emph-gn">Mountain-shaking, Earth-shattering Slash!</style>

5018103.Content: Your performance has impressed me... Let us face the final challenge head-on.

5018104.Content: Help Necalli break free from the undead's control!

5018200.Content: Behold-Maximo of the Kanamia, the scourge of the Byrnhald forces during the Asterleeds Independence War!

5018201.Content: Though your odds are grim, simply standing against Kanamian elites is a tale worth telling.

5018202.Content: Apologies, challengers! You have not met the conditions for the final trial!

5018204.Content: All events completed. Base objectives not achieved. You may manually leave the dungeon to retry!

5018205.Content: So much for the leisure time!

5019001.Content: There's a valley ahead. Perhaps... a brief moment of respite.

5019002.Content: Taltraud. So it was you all along...

5019003.Content: You still as pitiful as a sewer roach, I see.

5019004.Content: You really think you can defeat me?

5019005.Content: Cursed Asterleeds... I'll see you broken!

5019006.Content: Don't even think about escaping, all of you!

5019009.Content: <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, I'll find a way to shake them. See you in the ruins.

5020001.Content: Hold your <style="emph-gn">position</style> and don't let yourself be dragged back to the soul!

5020002.Content: The ancestral power of Kanamia infuses me. You'll regret your choice!

5020003.Content: Feeling confident? The trial has only just begun.

5020004.Content: Your soul has been split. Stay alert, its position is vital!

5020005.Content: A DoT field is forming. <style="emph-gn">Keep your distance from Allies and their souls!</style>

5020007.Content: They are undefeated, unmatched in every battle! They are...

5020008.Content: During the Asterleeds Independence War, they struck fear into Byrnhald. I give you-the Three Pioneers!

5020009.Content: Though your odds are grim, simply standing against Kanamian elites is a tale worth telling.

5020010.Content: I am not the only one <style="emph-gn">being tested here!</style>

5020011.Content: Oh... Sorry, challengers! I may have forgotten to warn you...

5020012.Content: No final trial for those who fall short in score!

5020013.Content: Alternatively, you could attempt the Mystery Trial for bonus score!

5025001.Content: Damn it! That one ran off that way!

5025002.Content: There must be something hidden-after him!

5025003.Content: Damn it! Is there even a path here? Let's climb over and check!

5025004.Content: Did we lose him? Curse this tree in the way... Let's retrace his steps.

5025005.Content: And damn it all... He broke my vase!
5025005.ChatName: A woman squats on the ground, quietly cleaning up the broken pieces.

5025006.Content: Judging by the trail... he likely went that way...

5025007.Content: It seems he climbed up from here. Let's take a look above!

5025008.Content: You're so slow! I've been waiting for ages!

5025010.Content: Blast it! I think I lost him!

5025011.Content: This trash can looks suspicious... Let's smash it and see what's inside.

5025014.Content: My friend, it's a bit rude to chase someone without an invitation.

5025015.Content: Don't let him escape-keep your eyes on him!

5025016.Content: He ran like the wind... seems he climbed that ladder!

5110001.Content: Follow the acceleration rings to reach the finish line

5110004.Content: The Nappoo is about to escape...

5110005.Content: (The ground is filled with yellow fireworks, with only one empty spot left. I want to light it there...)

5110006.Content: Congrats! You completed the entire "Lucky Firework Box" with yellow fireworks! May good fortune follow you always!

5110008.Content: A special choice! This one's called "Breath of the Forest Wanderer!" The healing green symbolizes a future of good health for you both!

5110009.Content: That's a good omen. How lovely!

5110010.Content: Excellent taste! This one's called "Heart of the Brave!" Lighting it means your adventure will be even more exciting!

5110011.Content: Yay! I declare this my favorite mini fireworks of the night!

5110012.Content: Speed Boarding experience is about to end! For another round, speak with Miss Splash!

5111003.Content: You seem quite energetic. Give it your all!

5111004.Content: Whoa! Yes! Just like that, keep it up!

5111006.Content: I have a feeling! This one's going to break the record!

5111007.Content: Relax, give it another try! You can definitely get a higher score!

5111008.Content: Score high by attacking the "Thunder Demon" within the time limit!

5203001.Content: (The Imagine Seed takes effect. Time and space seem to Frozen...)

5204001.Content: I can't catch him... Maybe I should return and see what Tina has discovered.

5206001.Content:
Denvel once told me that a Dominion duty is to achieve peace with the least possible sacrifice. But that philosophy... it doesn't suit this war.
The weight of his soldiers' deaths nearly crushed him. He clings to old memories just to escape the pain. Perhaps those memories were too vivid-they gave rise to an Imagine Seed.
Yet war has changed him. Denvel no longer seeks peace. Now, he craves victory. He's cast aside the man he once was... and become the nightmare of his enemies. Honestly, he frightens me more than the enemy ever could.
I hoped the Imagine seed would remind him of who he was-free him from his rage, and whatever darkness grips him. But... he rejected my offer. Has he truly decided to sacrifice himself for victory?
Still, I carry the seed with me. I fear what might happen if he continues down this path. I will stop him. I must.

-Jayden,
August, the 600th year of the Alician calendar

5206003.Content:
Dear Adventurers,
The Designer Guild cordially invites you to join us.
Outfits are essential for life and can tell your story. Like a warrior's weapon or a bard's song, what you wear reveals your thoughts, beliefs, happy or sad emotions, solitary lifestyle.
If you are interested,
Go to the Fashion Store in Entertainment District and talk to Sherry, our representative.
The Designer Guild

5206004.Content:
Dear Adventurers,
Whoever you are, wherever you're from-fishing is something no one can claim ignorance of. Be it pastime or profession, the lure of the water is eternal.
Should this call resonate with you, find your way to the Central District and speak with the Bluewave Anglers at the recruitment office.
The Bluewave Anglers

5206005.Content:
Dear Adventurers,
As strength blossoms, so too must the tools that carry it. The Artisan Guild now offers new services to assist adventurers in enhancing their gear.
If you are interested. Talk to Harvey at the Artisan Guild to learn how your weapons and armor may evolve alongside you.
Artisan Guild

5206006.Content:
Dear Adventurers,
The Culinary Guild welcomes you with open arms. In this world, nothing stirs the soul more than the aroma of food. Discovering a new recipe sparks more thrill than stumbling upon an uncharted island! Talk to Gordon on Food District and delve into the vibrant world of culinary wonders.
Culinary Guild

5220008.Content:
Choose the Surprise Card of destiny. Will you be the lucky one?


Now, there are 3 cards before you.
Two are blank, and one is the Lucky Card featuring adorable Ee-chan.

Step 1:
Choose one of the 3 cards, but don't flip it over yet.

Step 2:
We'll reveal one of the two remaining cards, and it'll be a blank one.

Step 3:
Now you have one chance to switch your card.
You have 2 choices:
→ Stick with your original card: Flip over the one you first chose.
→ Switch to the remaining card: Trade your card for the last unrevealed one and flip it over.
(Of course, if you choose to switch, you'll need to pay a small token... ^ ^)

If you flip over the Lucky Card with Ee-chan, then you're our chosen lucky one!
Note: Final interpretation rights for this game belong to the host.

Boss,

Once the job's done, we'll be waiting at home for your return, Boss.

Admiring you always,
Twin-Winged Bug

7020303.Content:
Who knows what that Man in Black is about... Completely unhinged! I never want to deal with such people again in my life!
Thank goodness, once we clear the bulk cargo, I can head back. I haven't forgotten the gift I promised. I'll bring it to you as soon as I can.
We owe the success of this deal to that well-informed subordinate. If he hadn't made contact with Neuler, I would never have known about this opportunity. Today he mentioned that an important figure who helped arrange this connection wants to meet me... (remainder of text lost)

Karl will help you.

Glory and riches-just one shot away.

10010101.Content:
To: The One Still Lost in Pillow Paradise,

Had a good rest?
I hope that by the time you read this, you'll be fully recharged and ready to go. I've left some brand-new clothes for you by the window-make sure you wear them properly, okay?
(As for your old outfit... it was a total disaster. I took care of it for you. You're welcome!)

Once you're all set, come find me downstairs-among the crowd, the most dazzling girl of them all, shining like starlight... no need to guess, that's me!

Looking forward to seeing you,
Airona

10010102.Content: Even if you're a legendary adventurer, I can't keep covering your tab like this...

10010103.Content: But I've accepted a new commission. Once it's done, I'll have the money to settle everything.

10010104.Content: Just give me a bit more time-I promise I'll pay it back.

10010105.Content: Even so, this is getting hard for me...

10010106.Content: It is the Seabreeze Festival in Asterleeds.

10010108.Content: Just beyond lies the Pioneer Bureau.

10010110.Content: Asterleeds, the melting pot of cultures, welcomes all-

10010112.Content: Let's head to Pioneer Bureau. Maybe they hold the answers we seek.

10010113.Content: Some troublesome little bird's causing chaos at the Seabreeze Festival! <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, be a dear and visit Arena Town to help out that glum purple-haired fellow.

10010114.Content: (First of all... Shall we check the Anchor Notes?)

10010200.Content: <style="emph-gn">(Another Teleportal... Since we're here, might as well activate it.)</style>

10010202.Content: Obviously-we first obtain the <style="emph-gn">adventurer's mandatory credentials</style>. The Pioneer Bureau isn't some back-alley club, you know!

10010203.Content: Prepare in advance any materials that can prove your abilities-it will make the official registration process much smoother!

10010204.Content: Airona, you seem pretty familiar with the Pioneer Bureau, don't you?

10010206.Content: That was quite a flight. You've truly mastered the strength of the Talents.

10010207.Content: Next, we return to Asterleeds to investigate the source of the Void Engram.

10010208.Content: Feels pretty damn good to ride the wind, doesn't it?

10010209.Content: Sure does... Alright, prepare for landing.

10010210.Content: Something is off about this place...

10010211.Content: Here it is... Just as I feared-the demi-humans in this place have all been eroded by Void Corruption.

10010213.Content: Something's off about this place... Stay sharp.

10010215.Content: There's something unusual up ahead. Let's go investigate.

10010216.Content: Follow this road and you'll soon arrive at the Pioneer Bureau.

10010218.Content: Naturally, Asterleeds is celebrating the Seabreeze Festival.

10010220.Content: The Seabreeze Festival marks the city-state's independence.

10010221.Content: Every home displays sea lilies by their doors, symbols of blessings and peace.

10010222.Content: If we're lucky, we might catch sight of Vita and Rab-the festival's mascot cats.

10010223.Content: And let's not forget the romantic legends tied to the festival. I'll tell you all about them later.

10010224.Content: The Pioneer Bureau is just ahead-don't forget to activate the Engram Hub here!

10010227.Content: Come on, we need to see what's happening!

10010229.Content: It seems a fierce battle broke out here.

10010232.Content: There's something unusual up ahead. Let's go investigate.

10010233.Content: Watch your step, everyone. We'll be safe once we reach Asterleeds!

10010234.Content: How's the wound? Honestly... you shouldn't have followed me.

10010235.Content: It's not too bad, but... I don't think I can walk back alone. My legs won't stop shaking.

10010236.Content: Don't worry. I'll take you back myself.

10010238.Content: These black energies... Damn it, everyone, be on your guard!

10010239.Content: (Tina gave me a Loot Opening Voucher. I should be able to use it now.)

10010240.Content: (What a strange dream... But even if it was just a dream, everything felt so vivid... and familiar...)

10010241.Content: (Forget it for now. There's a letter on the cabinet beside the bed. Could it be for me?)

10010242.Content: Olvera should be somewhere in Arena Town to the north. Let's go find her.

10010245.Content: She might be inside the Cliff Ruins. We should keep moving forward.

10010246.Content: The Cliff Ruins is right there inside. The Void Engram... it's thick. Why would it gather here of all places? Stay sharp.

10010247.Content: See that <style="emph-gn">purple-haired fellow</style> over there? He's a staff for the Festival. Let's go talk to him.

10010259.Content:
To {*me.name*}: Make good use of this "Asterleeds Chaos Survival Guide!" As the sworn rival of Brave Kitten, you must not act like a reckless rookie!

1. Always keep a box of Healing Aromatic in your backpack: For emergencies, to prevent sudden fainting.
2. To enhance your weapon: Go to the Artisan Guild and find a Legacy expert. There's nothing they can't handle.
3. Pack sufficient food when heading out: Eating a little more won't hurt...
4. For more treasure chests: Wander around the plains more often (Be careful of dark mist and monsters recently).


> Don't say "You're so cute" to monsters (they might take it seriously...)
> Don't take on Miss Valeria's "absolutely safe" commissions.
> Don't believe Miss Valeria when she says "this mission is very simple."
Don't bully friendly little animals, such as kitties, puppies, chicks, and Boarlets!


Several essential adventure items are enclosed. Looking forward to a fair fight with you!

Your sworn enemy, the star-blessed Brave Kitten, Narulu.

10010261.Content: Everyone, be careful! These monsters are getting up again!

10010262.Content: Oh no, it's a Flame Orc... It's been corrupted too...

10010263.Content: Now is a good chance to defeat it!

10010265.Content: Oh no, there's a strong Void Engram presence ahead! And the howls of monsters, sounds like there are quite a few of them.

10010269.Content: There's a strange rift ahead. Let's go check it out.

10010274.Content: At this rate, Thunder Demon might have to be renamed Charm Demon instead...

10010301.Content: That being said, where is Tina?

10010302.Content: At times like this, she usually wanders around Entertainment District to see if there are any new trinkets from out of town.

10010303.Content: As long as it's a product from out of town, Tina will look at it for a long time.

10010306.Content: For certain reasons, Tina cannot leave the Asterleeds jurisdiction. So she's curious about things from outside the city...

10010307.Content: But it's strange... Even if Abeku is the culprit, why would he steal someone else's diary?

10010308.Content: When we see that guy, let's ask him together and get to the bottom of it!

10010310.Content: Eek, these people got beaten up so badly by Tina.<style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, let's go!

10010311.Content:
Alician Calendar Year 602: Protective Measures Enacted for Tina

Following the restoration of the Hruga Seal, Tina's unique identity became a matter of continental security across Magna.
Due to potential risks, the majority of council members advocated for protective measures. This decision came with restrictions on Tina's freedom—she would be confined to the Asteria Plains.
Tina ultimately understood and accepted the terms of this protection order. The measure was smoothly implemented under the supervision of Olvera, Defense Corps Commander.

10010312.Content:
Alician Calendar Year 608: Reassessment of Tina's Identity and Power

Amid past unrest, Tina repeatedly defended Asteris, proving her strength and loyalty. Even under scrutiny, she quietly continued to protect the city.
Voices began to rise within the Council—Tina has shown she can safeguard both herself and Asteris. Her power and contributions deserve proper recognition, and she should be posthumously awarded the Hero Medal.
As time passed, this proposal gained the support of the majority of council members.

10010313.Content:
Last night at 22:00, Tina's file, stored in the council hall, was stolen. At 22:10, I dispatched the Corps to find the suspect, while also having Jerrad issue a commission as a backup plan.
Today at 13:30, I learned the commission was accepted. Not long after, at 13:50, Tina brought in Abeku. He confessed that he had already met with the buyer but still had a few remaining pages of the file.
To find the remaining pages, I went to the Pioneer Bureau to inquire with the guide. I only obtained the clue "a powerful green-haired beautiful girl and a clear-eyed adventurer duo."
Combining this with Jerrad's recent eyewitness testimony at the Festival, I believe the ones who accepted the commission were Lady Airona and her new companion.
To find the remaining file pages as soon as possible, I contacted all Seabreeze Festival stall owners to help find them. I know Lady Airona dislikes trouble, and my making such a big fuss will surely annoy her.
... But for the safety of Asterleeds and Tina, please forgive me, mentor.
However, five minutes later, Tina returned to the Corps. She had already brought back the file! Only after communicating with her did I understand the status of the incident on your end.
I am very sorry. It was my impatience that offended the beloved Lady Airona and the respected {*me.name*}.
If there is any compensation I can offer, please do not hesitate to ask...

10010314.Content:
Appetizer "Supreme - Cold Infusion Platter"
· Lightly Chilled Drink with Abyssal Fish Sashimi
· Berry Jam Marinated Fragrant Steamed Fruit
- Asterleeds' proud seabreeze specialty, an elegant and cool taste, awaiting your tasting.

Main Course "Braver's Sizzling Steak"
- A legend belonging to adventurers. Sizzling hot 3000°C stone slab grilling on site, dedicated only to you who pursue quality.

Special Recommendation! Drink "Journey with the Snow Knight"
- Inspired by the urban legend, the Snow Knight of the Plains. This brew keeps you cool even in midsummer.

Special Recommendation! Dessert "Dizzy Void Monster"
- Chocolate ice cream ball inspired by the ancient secret - Void Engram. Sweet things can also be very mysterious.
10010314.ChatName: A Tastebud Journey of Romance and Seabreeze

10010315.Content:
-"Let Splendor Bloom"-
Hosts: Valeria, Jerrad

Opening Dance "Fluffy Wuffy Waltz"
Starring: Mascots (Vita, Rab, Ee-chan)

Martial Arts Performance "Tough Guy, Open Heart"
