10010315.ChatName: Third Seabreeze Festival - Fireworks Festival Opening Ceremony

10010316.Content: Walk along the seaside, and just before the Council Building, you'll find the venue for the opening ceremony.

10010317.Content: There are troopers patrolling the road all the time.

10010318.Content: Well, after all, Void Engram appeared again, and a confidential file was lost...

10010319.Content: Just in case, let's pay more attention to any abnormal situations.

10010320.Content: (There're some abnormal black sigils on the ground, it's the aura of the Man in Black. Follow these sigil to find him!)

10010322.Content: Ha, thank you all for listening to the poem I wrote this year. I look forward to your continued support next year!

10010323.Content: Please wait a moment, everyone. Our award ceremony will begin shortly.

10010325.Content: All Asterleeds Defense Corps soldiers, prepare to clear the Void Engram and protect the people!

10010327.Content:
Esteemed {*me.name*},

The Seabreeze Festival was suddenly struck by the Void Engram. Thank you for your willingness to help the Asterleeds Defense Corps and protect the safety of the citizens.
Tina is in grave danger. As her close friend and comrade-in-arms, I must go to her rescue.
Though circumstances prevent me from thanking you in person, please accept this letter as a token of my gratitude and sincere apologies.

Olvera

10010330.Content: Why do people keep leaving messages for us... This isn't right.

10010331.Content: Everyone! Stay calm and evacuate in order!

10010332.Content: By the way, what is The Spinning Rudder?

10010333.Content: That's the most famous restaurant in town! They've just launched a Seabreeze Festival Special. Let's go try it!

10010334.Content:
{*me.name*}:
Need your help with Tina, meet me at Cliff Ruins!
-Airona

10010401.Content: The Fireworks Festival won't start for a while yet. Let's wander around nearby and see if there's anything fun!

10010402.Content: It's almost time, <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, let's go to the seaside!

10010403.Content: Adventurer, please take care of the 3 nearby Void Prisms.

10010404.Content: All civilians have been rescued. Thank you for your help, adventurer. Please head to a safe zone and rest.

10090101.Content: Is this Lallipar? It feels a bit deserted.

10090103.Content: (The villagers who used to gather beneath the old tree to chat have vanished...)

10090104.Content: (The children who filled the streets with laughter are nowhere to be seen.)

10090105.Content: (Where have the diligent folk of Lallipar gone?)

10090106.Content: (The Caprahorns wander the fields unattended, seemingly indifferent to the absence of their owners.)

10090107.Content: (No one answers the knock at Fafala's door. It seems Fafala isn't home.)

10090108.Content: (Outside the warehouse, crates are stacked-two colors, but both brimming with Starsoul Flasks.)

10090109.Content: (Better keep them separated just in case.)

10090110.Content: Adventurer, thank you for always looking after us.

10090111.Content: When I grow weary, I think of you and remind myself: I must endure.

10090112.Content: I want to be brave, like you-to support those around me...

10120101.Content: You haven't found that bastard's hideout yet? Are you sure you searched thoroughly? Damn it... If those files get leaked...

10120102.Content: Report to Lord Jerrad! I... I'm not sure!

10120103.Content: Fine. Everyone, get it together and stand tall!

10120104.Content: By the hair of Lamond... someone help, anyone!

10120106.Content: The volume's too low. Try again!

10120108.Content: (Looks like I'll have to take a more direct approach to make him talk...)

10120201.Content: Bertram mentioned their contact token was a special drink... Want to try mixing one, pal?

10120204.Content: I still can't believe he was the traitor... It's true what they say-never judge by appearances.

10120301.Content: Rab? Rab! Aren't you the Seabreeze Festival mascot? Why are you hiding from us?

10120302.Content: Hmph, the lazy kitty won't even play with us...

10120303.Content: This Rab is too apathetic! We should report it to the Pioneer Bureau!

10120401.Content: Happy Seabreeze Festival! Welcome. Right this way to the Pioneer Bureau!

10120402.Content: Want to become a bonafide adventurer? Sign up now!

10120403.Content: Damn it... When will I finally become an adventurer?

10120404.Content: It's a holiday today-why are these poor kitties still working?!

10120405.Content: Hey there! A friend I haven't met yet!

10120501.Content: (I wonder how Airona's investigation is going...)

10120601.Content: By the hair of Lamond... someone help, anyone!

10130101.Content: Will these things harm anyone passing by?

10130102.Content: I doubt it. They're just leftover traces. The real threat is the Void Engram itself.

10130103.Content: We need to find it quickly...

10130201.Content: If we keep moving forward, we'll reach the meeting hall, right? I think there's an event scheduled there today...

10130204.Content: We must inform the Asterleeds Defense Corps immediately.

10130205.Content: I only hope we're not too late...

10130301.Content: The trail of Void Engram ends here, but it must still be close.

10130302.Content: Jerrad was nearby as well-we decided to ask for his help.

10130303.Content: (The traces of Void Engram... they all point in the same direction...)

10130304.Content: If Void Engram has seeped into the city, it must have left signs. Keep your eyes open-move ahead and investigate.

10130306.Content: But why would he hide all this? What is he waiting for...? Let's check the area over there.

10130307.Content: Come on, the ceremony is just ahead!

10130309.Content: These black energies... Damn it, everyone, be on your guard!

10130401.Content: Lady Airona! And is that... a new recruit with you?

10130601.Content: All of the finest forging masters in Asterleeds-and perhaps the entire continent-belong to the Artisan Guild!

10130602.Content: Just to be safe, I'd like the Smelting to prepare a weapon suited to you before we meet the Commander.

10130603.Content: You helped me today-consider the cost covered.

10130605.Content: Hey, don't be so formal with me!

10140101.Content: Tina once served as my adjutant. On the battlefield, we moved like twin blades.

10140102.Content: She was my second set of hands and eyes. I could trust her in any situation.

10140103.Content: Though... that doesn't seem to be the case anymore.

10140104.Content: Something changed between us. Perhaps you'll come to understand it, in time.

10140105.Content: Your turn to speak, adventurer. The Void Engram has crept into both the plains and the city-what's your take?

10140106.Content: Maybe it's the work of the same forces behind the spy we uncovered.

10140107.Content: If only it were that simple...

10140201.Content: I think I heard Lady Airona, <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>.

10140301.Content: (Wait... something's appeared where Tina stood before...?)

10140302.Content: (No-stay focused. We'll investigate later. I only hope Tina's safe...)

10140303.Content: (The Void Engram and the Medal... It's time to investigate their connection.)

10200102.Content: (The messenger... were they dressed as a doll?)

10200106.Content: (Miss Blonde...? So it was Rab who sent the letter to Valeria!)

10200201.Content: (Tina should be somewhere around Entertainment District. Let's take a look.)

10410101.Content: We're at the border of the Kanamia Tribe!

10410102.Content: (I wonder how Airona and Olvera are faring...)

10410103.Content:
Travelers of the Tide: "Do not enter the tribe before dusk.
Where kindling flames flicker,
heed the moon's phases."

10410104.Content:
Travelers of the Tide:
"Between the beckoning stream and the crashing falls, the moon's phases bestow its gift."

10410105.Content:
Travelers of the Tide:
"Within the folds of this letter lies a gift, a veil against the scent of the world beyond.
Draped in its embrace, you become one with nature.
Only then may you step into the village, what you seek lies in our hallowed grounds.
But tread lightly-night has fallen, and the weight of dew clings to the earth, each step a whisper in the dark."

10410106.Content: (Everyone's preparing to leave. I should change and be on my way.)

10410107.Content: (Someone's speaking. Perhaps their words will lead us to the Forbidden Zone.)

10410108.Content: (They mentioned a "spring blessed by the ancestors" that heals wounds... Could such a thing truly exist?)

10410109.Content: (Even Kanamians can't enter the Forbidden Zone... This won't be easy.)

10410110.Content: (No useful information yet. Let's try somewhere else.)

10410111.Content: (The blessing ritual seems to hold deep importance for their tribe.)

10410112.Content: (Let me organize everything I've learned so far.)

10410114.Content: This is the arena for the Kanamia Brave Selection. Let's sign up!

10410116.Content: I'm off to hunt! <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, don't come back empty-handed!

10410117.Content: Warriors! Today, the Kanamian ancestors shall witness your resolve and courage!

10410118.Content: I hereby declare the Kanamia Brave Trial... begins!

10410119.Content: Will the victorious warrior please step forward? I wish to speak with you privately.

10410801.Content: Ow, ow, ow... That one didn't count! Let's go again!

10410802.Content: Th-this is part of the plan! It wasn't a mistake!

10410803.Content: How about this move? Bet you've never seen it before!

10410804.Content: He's got an opening! On your left-think you can dodge it, or not?

10410805.Content: This time it's towards the right-don't get distracted!

10410806.Content: You're my opponent? Then show me what you've got!

10410807.Content: Tch, this is actually getting interesting!

10410809.Content: Just so you know, I won't go easy on you.

10410810.Content: Let me see what you're made of!

10410811.Content: Keep going, keep going. Stay focused!

10420101.Content: Oh! Friends, come closer-let us talk!

10420102.Content: There's something over there... a log?

10420103.Content: The spark of hope lies in my hand. Please... take it back to Kanamia.

10420104.Content: (Could the ghost of Yaretsi... know why I'm here? This is all so fascinating...)

10430101.Content: Priestess! We want to go in to see <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>. He's been out of contact for too long!

10430102.Content: I'm counting on you, too, Rorola!

10430103.Content: There's no need to worry. Listen closely, he's back.

10430104.Content: Priestess! We want to go in to see <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>. She's been out of contact for too long!

10430105.Content: There's no need to worry. Listen closely, she's back.

10430106.Content: Wait a minute, look over there!

10430107.Content: Rorola, wait! It's dangerous up ahead!

10430108.Content: A Engram Anomaly hit just now, and that black pillar of light indicates Denvel must've done something again.

10430109.Content: It's a Void Sigil... We're running out of time!

10430110.Content: Damn it, are we too late again?

10430111.Content: Let's go regroup with Lady Airona.

10430112.Content: Everyone, please quiet down. I have something to say.

10430114.Content: <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, we couldn't have made it this far without you. Just one last step!

10430117.Content: Kanamia Brave <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, please use the final key and open the gate to the Forbidden Zone.

10430118.Content: Use [Phantom Dash] to shatter the wind barrier.

10430301.Content: Hey! Are you okay? Can you hear me?

10430302.Content: It was them... the Dark Mist Legion...

10430303.Content: Get some rest. I swear, this won't have been in vain.

10430304.Content: It's time to go deal with this Anomaly.

10510103.Content: I don't understand. How did it come to this?

10510104.Content: (It seems to have stopped spreading... But the Void Sigil remains...)

10510209.Content:
To the Friends of Narulu,

By the time you read this, my husband and I will have already evacuated with the Asterleeds Defense Corps. Please, do not worry for our safety.

We know all too well the plains are suffering a disaster unlike anyone has seen before. This is all the doing of the Dark Mist Legion and their leader, Denvel. They are the ones who brought about Narulu's tragic fate.

The path you walk is filled with danger. You must not be burdened by the sorrows of the past. Let this sorrow be ours to bear.

Please, take care of yourselves, and be ever vigilant.
May the sea breeze answer your will and bless your journey.

Agnes

10510210.Content: The Asterleeds Defense Corps is reliable as always. The Engram Collectors are already in place.

10510211.Content: <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, am I seeing things? There's something stuck to the Engram Collector...

10510213.Content: With that, all three Void Sigils are fading. Now, we...

10510301.Content: That's Jerrad! <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, let's go help him!

10510303.Content: Damn it... more of them are breaking through!

10520101.Content: Tatta vanishes in a blink! What now?!

10520102.Content: Such a mess! I couldn't see where he went...

10520103.Content: He's not fully recovered yet. Oh, please...

10520105.Content:
{*me.name*}, it's time we moved on.
There's still no sign of Denvel. Our next move is to rendezvous with Lady Airona-then we'll plan our course from there.

10520108.Content:
West of the harbor, where light gives way to a murky veil.
North of the forest, where shadows weave through the mist.
By the reclaimed wasteland, the silence lingers.
Beneath the dome, the end of all things draw near.

10520301.Content: Tina told me everything. Thank you, <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, for everything you've done.

10520302.Content: Is everything alright on Dorothy' side?

10520303.Content: Now's not the time to dwell on this. Once she reads her uncle's letter... the choice must be hers alone.

10520312.Content: The presence of Void Mist grows increasingly powerful...

10520313.Content: I hope we're still in time...

10530201.Content:
"{*me.name*}, welcome back!"

Tina runs straight toward me and wraps me in a tight hug. Standing beside her is Olvera, visibly exhausted.

The silver-haired commander says nothing. She gives a faint smile and nods at me in silence.

Then comes Airona. She stares at me as if she had something to say. But in the end, she says nothing. She simply smiles, clear and gentle as spring water.

Only when I see them all again... I realize the long shadow cast over the plains... is finally gone.

10530301.Content: I told you-this woman is tainted. She's unworthy to fight for Asterleeds!

10530302.Content: (Now of all times, someone still has the nerve to stir trouble?)

10540101.Content: <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, let's begin. You know what to do!

10540103.Content: Please, Tina, stay with me... Don't close your eyes...

10540105.Content: Hang in there, Tina!! We're almost there!!

10540201.Content:
1. Long ago, during the era when the Divine governed Regnus, the planet's Engram was abundant. Where this strength converged, Stellariums formed, and from their power crystallized the Core of Stellarium.
2. The arrogant Igdias once sought to monopolize the Stellariums, only to be driven out by the Divine-yet not before stealing several Core of Stellarium.
3. Hruga's strength stems from the Core of Stellarium, a force that has become inseparable from her very being. Yet, such a fusion is not without consequence-
for when the Core of Stellarium binds itself to a mortal, it inevitably bends to the wielder's spiritual strength. In time, Hruga drew upon the power of the Void Engram, an act that tainted and eroded both her own heart and the Core of Stellarium itself.

10540301.Content: (Jerrad, Valeria, Dorothy... They're at The Double-Faced Coin too!)

10540302.Content: (It's getting late. I should head upstairs and rest.)

10540303.Content:
You looked so peaceful sleeping yesterday, I couldn't bring myself to pull back your blanket...

The mist still hung low, and that island had long since vanished into the deep blueou've been working so hard. Take all the rest you need.

Once you've had your fill of sleep, come find me downstairs.

There's something important I need to tell you.
Airona

10610102.Content: The monsters are getting more and more aggressive... Adventurer, my house is nearby. If you trust me, I can take care of the unconscious lady for now...

10620101.Content: Just as expected-they turned us away. But from the guard's words, it sounds like caravans are still being let through.

10620201.Content: Then we've no other choice... Let's move!

10620301.Content: Ow... my stomach. I can't take another step...

10630101.Content: Careful. The path is narrow and the ground's uneven.

10630102.Content: You've got a good eye finding this hidden road.

10630104.Content: Oh dear... too many uninvited guests.

10630201.Content: (Holding the ore in one's hand, I can immediately sense the immense Engram within-its purity and scale far surpassing human imagination.)

10630202.Content: (The Sislaetha Mines is under the strict control of the Blackstone Squad-better steer clear of their patrols.)

10630203.Content: The light inside the bottle has gone out... Did it work?

10630204.Content: (He remains weak and feeble, but his complexion has visibly improved.)

10630206.Content: Cough-hack! I... I'm not being taken away...?

10630301.Content: Damn... We need to avoid these people-can't risk causing trouble for the miners!

10630302.Content: Oh, no... Miss Airona fainted! Hey-are you alright?!

10630303.Content: I'm sorry. I didn't expect her to react so badly...

10630304.Content: What should I do now... Wait, the Starsoul Flask! Can that help?!

10810101.Content: Even disguised as traveling merchants, we're walking a fine line. If we're caught red-handed, it'll mean real trouble.

10810104.Content: We shouldn't linger here. We need to move-fast.

10810105.Content: Heh! You're telling me! Let's move our asses already!

10810106.Content:
Milo should be nearby.
Grieg said he's wearing a red hat-shouldn't be hard to spot.

10810201.Content: Wait-Mr. Breck left something. Hold on, I'll return it.

10810202.Content: No... I think he meant for us to have this.

10810203.Content:
Ugh, locked...
{*me.name*}, where's the key? Let's take it out and give it a try!

10810204.Content: (The key fit perfectly. A soft click echoed-locked from within.)

10810205.Content:
Sorry about this, but we need to defend ourselves.
Hope you can understand.

10810206.Content: (Take this path to get down there.)

10810207.Content: (It seems a blade stands driven into the ground.)

10810301.Content: The bandages are soaked in blood. He must be seriously injured. This isn't good...

10810302.Content:
The footprints are sparse and chaotic-
few Dave personnel, and they evacuated in a hurry.

10810304.Content: These monsters are becoming more aggressive. I hope Dave and his team are still holding out.

10810305.Content: Dave never backed down, even when cornered. We won't give up on him so early. Let's keep going.

10810307.Content:
The Ruby yield plummeted by at least 30% compared to last year. The National Research Institute is barely operational. The duke is furious. Shouldn't Chris give a proper explanation?! Yet instead of showing up himself, he sent his aide, Reiner, to brush us off! We must report this neglect to the duke when we return...

(The paper, pristine in its craftsmanship-white, supple, untouched by the passage of time. Yet, the notebook bore the scars of neglect, its pages marred by ochre stains, fused together in stubborn resistance. Sticky to the touch, they refused to yield.)

10820101.Content:
These machines are roaring non-stop-my head's pounding...
{*me.name*}, I'll leave the investigation to you. Find out where the ore is sourced and where it's shipped.

10820102.Content:
Mmm-hmm, understood.
The ore comes in through here and feeds directly into the smelting furnace.

10820103.Content: Hmm... So these are the finished goods ready for shipping. Pretty obvious there's no Ruby visible in the crates.

10820104.Content:
This area's still part of the smeltery... and they say slag is buried here.
But are we sure it's only slag?

10820201.Content: The ore crates on the vehicle are stacked neatly-fully inspection-proof, free of any contraband substances.

10820202.Content: Maybe we could look for surveillance blind spots?

10820203.Content: That aura... it's the same as Hruga's! <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, is there any way to get closer?

10820204.Content: Is everything operating normally with the smelting equipment?

10820205.Content: This is a... serious matter. We won't take it lightly. You have our word.

10830101.Content:
Darya had left a mark behind.
A carved arrow pointed deeper into the mining zone.

10830102.Content:
The Squad has outposts everywhere... If they're alerted, the miners are doomed.
{*me.name*}, we'll need to move quietly.

10830103.Content: Are the miners okay, I wonder...

10830201.Content: Is Boyce worried we'll mess this up?

10830202.Content: Whatever happens, I have to fulfill the mission Master Lothar entrusted to me. Every change in the mine must be reported.

10830205.Content: What on earth is going on... Let's go find out.

10830206.Content: We'll need to create a distraction. Get the sentry's attention.

10830208.Content: When you head out, always carry a change of clothes.

10830209.Content: During travels, when unexpected situations arise, whipping out an emergency kit is always the right move!

10830210.Content: This jar contains the wind from that stormy night in Asterleeds. It must've meant something special to Tina.

10830211.Content: True to its name, the jar encapsulates Asterleeds' gentle sea breeze, its rhythm whispering through the air like a quiet pulse of the city.

10830212.Content: The wind, gathered during Seabreeze Festival, carried with it the echoes of countless voices, especially when taking a deep breath.

17100101.Content:
From her very first day at the Guild, Emeria's brilliance shone through.
Confronted with the underpowered first-generation Engram Engine, she dared to propose radical improvements-
many of which were eventually adopted by the Chief Artisan, ushering in the creation of the second-generation Engram Engine.
Engram Engine would go on to power not only wooden fishing boats but small ships, thanks to her contributions.
More crucially, it achieved mass production of Engram Engine, enabling its widespread application in maritime domains.

Yet Emeria's vision reached further still.
Though the Bapharian Legacy far surpasses current technology, she believes it hindered sustainable growth.
Humanity, she warned, had built upon foundations it did not comprehend.

To forge a new path, she invented the "Astral Differentiator," a steam-and-gear-driven computational device.
At the time, the differentiator was widely employed for calculating complex parameters-utilizing no Bapharian Legacy whatsoever.
This invention earned her the prestigious Ocean Platinum Card, personally awarded by the Council Chair.

Yet, her life was cut short at the pinnacle of triumph.
Tragically, Emeria perished in an experiment at merely 42 years of age.

17100102.Content: It's empty... Let's split up and search for the differentiator.

17100103.Content: Adventurer! Over here-this might be it: "Instructions for Operating the Astral Differentiator!"

17100104.Content:
1. Preheat the machine
- Open the coal storage compartment and ignite the coal.
- Monitor the temperature gauge and wait until it reaches 100.

2. Switch to calculation mode
- Insert the punched card into the upper-right probe socket, then quickly retreat from the machine.
- Await the completion of computational gearset switching.

*Never touch the machine while the traction cable is in motion!

3. Input calculation parameters
- Rotate the input wheel to the designated position.
- Do not lean against the gear assemblies.

4. Begin calculation
- Activate the steam valve located at the machine's top-left.
- Stand by for computation completion.

5. Output Results
- Calculation may take anywhere from seconds to several minutes.
- Wait quietly for the T-hammer to print the computed results.

17100107.Content:
When you read this note, I bring you glad tidings:
This island now belongs to you. Make haste-travel to Ocean Hill and register its coordinates without delay.

And since you've stepped onto this Misty Island, my mission may yet endure.
The box with the needle attached is my flight data box-used to record all aerial parameters.
It marks the last beacon left by my shattered ornithopter and proves that it crossed the unknown skies and arrived on the far side.

I beg you-carry it to the Asterleeds Artisan Guild.
It alone bears witness that someone as ordinary as I once pierced what seemed an insurmountable barrier.
It alone holds the key for humanity to defy the so-called curse of the skies and soar freely once more.

17100108.Content:
Seven years ago, during a high-stress trial of the Engram Engine II, the system failed-and in that moment, I brushed against the very edge of technological possibility.
The coordinates were clearly within reach, yet an invisible force barred all passage. That island...
it stands as both the furthest boundary our ships can reach and the line I have never been able to cross.

And yet, the more impossible the barrier seemed, the deeper my desire grew to overcome it.
It was then that I turned my gaze skyward-toward a path long forsaken by others, and thus devoted myself to aircraft research and development.
The first ornithopter soon took shape. Though countless simulations confirmed the data's accuracy, each test flight ended in failure.
Undeterred, I delved into ancient manuscripts, forgotten blueprints, and the scattered remnants of past endeavors. Each account, without exception, pointed to a chilling truth:
whenever the aircraft approached a certain altitude, it vanished-erased with surgical precision by an unknown force.

Something-beyond the grasp of our current technology-seemed to guard the skies, enforcing a boundary none had crossed.

But I have never been one to yield to the unknown. And so, I chose to ascend myself.
Only by confronting it directly could I hope to uncover the truth-whether beyond that mist lies nature's forbidden zone-or the domain of some unseen will.
Though the path forward is veiled in fog, and the journey may well lead to peril, I find myself without the option to turn back.

17100109.Content:
Even before I departed, I understood the cost-this flight was a gamble with life itself.
In the old fables, a father and son dared to chase the sun with wings of wax. Their ambition ended in tragedy, their wings melted by the heat, their bodies claimed by the sea.
-Now, standing on the edge of the unknown, I find myself not so different from them.

But my friend, do not mourn me.

In the final moment, as the ornithopter was torn apart mid-air, I experienced a clarity unlike any I've ever known!

I glimpsed the truth-that shroud of mist is no natural phenomenon, but a barrier imbued with will!
Though my ornithopter collapsed under the immense force, its destruction was not in vain. That moment of failure yielded our most precious discovery:
The so-called "insurmountable" boundary proved otherwise-it left behind measurable data, evidence that its limits are not beyond reach.

17100110.Content: I found it! Adventurer- over here, quickly!

17100111.Content:
This data box holds the final fragments of my journey-the knowledge I wrested from "it" at the very cost of my life.
In those last seconds, the data box captured invaluable evidence:
Surges of eerie heatwaves, hyper-directional pressure, and energy pulses powerful enough to cripple any device...

Please, take this data box back with you-every bit of truth we've uncovered is locked inside.
Take it to the Artisan Guild-and tell them this: Emeria, the one who dared to defy the unknown, didn't fail.
Her body may have been broken, but before the end, she hurled a spear at the invisible wall.
Yes-human creation can pierce the forbidden sky.

The complete designs for ornithopters are recorded in those notebooks labeled "ASH," locked away in the Guild's basement vault.
With the parameters contained in this data box, the design can be perfected. The curse that binds us to the earth can be broken!

Though my flesh may rot here, this data box will become the wind beneath the wings of all who dare to follow.
Let the will of humankind rewrite the rules of this world!

20110107.Content:
Subject: Joint Investigation into Recent Seabreeze Festival Anomalies
Reference Number: WT-608-VII-■■■
People in Charge: Tina, Valeria

Event A: Plain Ghost Incident
Mysterious mist has appeared on the Astria Plains. Creatures exposed to the mist show signs of confusion and increased aggression.
It has been confirmed that the mist is the Void Mist, an evil force that swept the continent three years ago, wielded by the witch Hruga.
The Man in Black involved in this incident faked his death immediately upon discovery and disappeared. According to witnesses, the Man in Black acted exaggeratedly and is suspected to follow the Void Mist.

Event B: Tina File Loss Incident
The night before the Seabreeze Festival, Tina's secret files were stolen. Investigation shows the thief was Abeku from the black market while the buyer remained masked and dressed in black.
According to Abeku's testimony, the buyer's behavior closely matches the suspect in Incident A, suggesting they may be the same person.

Event C: Ceremony Explosion Incident
At the Seabreeze Festival fireworks opening, Tina's Seabreeze Medal was sabotaged, causing the Void Mist to explode during the ceremony.


[The following content is TOP SECRET!]


Tina suffered from Void Corruption and was trapped in the Cliff Ruins. She was rescued with the help of the adventurer {*me.name*}.
Other witnesses report that Tina's attacker is the black-clad person involved in Incidents A and B, linking the three cases and revealing a conspiracy targeting Tina.

Investigation Results

The Man in Black can freely use Void Engram and targets Tina. This individual is highly likely a follower of Hruga.
Tina is one of the guardians sealing the witch. The attack on Tina is likely motivated by a desire to break the witch's seal and release Hruga.
All parties must stay alert to the witch's movements and keep tracking the Man in Black.

20120106.Content:
Alician calendar, August ■■■, Year 600, Rainy

Rain drums on the tent like a death knell.

I remember Denvel saying: "A true commander fights for peace. Blind sacrifice is meaningless." He always used to say that, but now we're all lingering on the verge of death.

I saw his armor stained red with my own eyes. Each red stain corresponded to a face that would never smile again. He now spends all day caressing that terrible weapon. More than once, I've stumbled upon him in the trenches, muttering the names of fallen comrades to the empty air. Over time, his obsession actually condensed into a visible crystal, like a teardrop-shaped piece of amber... The Imagine Seed traps him in his memories.

But the enemy won't give us time to dream. During the surprise attack the day before yesterday, Denvel ordered the destruction of the civilian evacuation route. When the light of the explosion reflected on his face, I saw,for the first time, the devil's reflection in the Dominion eyes.

This morning, I secretly slipped the Imagine Seed into his overcoat pocket. It was supposed to be the key to saving his last shred of humanity. But he dropped the water cup as if scalded, the crystal shards glinting faintly on the muddy ground like a small corpse. I dare not guess what was hidden in his final gaze. Was it disgust? Anger? Or... fear?

This seed is about to sprout in my pocket. I must do something, before it's too late...

20410108.Content:
I am sorry... so terribly sorry.

I have committed an unforgivable crime. A coward, a fool, a sinner in the eyes of Asterleeds—this is what I have become.

But for the sake of my wife and children, there was no other choice.

It was the Dark Mist Legion... they coerced me into this. But why? They should have been ■■■ three years ago. Is it truly possible that ■■■ still exist in this world?

This afternoon, I will obey the orders given to me and proceed to Ancient City of Vill. This is the price I must pay.

The fireworks last night were the last beautiful sight I will ever see. I'm sorry, my dear wife, my children—I can't join you to celebrate the Seabreeze Festival this year...

If anyone finds this letter, please deliver my apologies to Lady Tina.

I am so sorry, Lady Tina. My cowardice has brought harm upon you, and I am not worthy of asking for forgiveness...I only wish that the Divine would bless you and keep you safe, and that you may survive the coming storm...

Last words
Ryan

20410109.Content:
Document content:
Document No.: 58
Dark Mist Legion Investigation Record

January, Year 600, Alician calendar
The war began with Byrnhald's Vanguard landing in the Andra Basin. The Andra Landing Battle lasted nearly two months, and the enemy was almost entirely destroyed. However, after the conflict, it became clear that some remnants of the Dark Mist Legion had survived and retreated deep into the plains with their leader, Denvel.

September, Year 600, Alician calendar
In the midst of the war, the Deputy Squad Leader of the Dark Mist Legion, Jayden, along with his reconnaissance team, infiltrated our ranks. Though the reconnaissance operation was thwarted, they were not apprehended. The Asterleeds Defense Corps later received reliable intel confirming that Jayden's team had entered the Towering Ruin during their retreat. None of them survived, and what they encountered in those ruins remains a mystery.

September, Year 601, Alician calendar
A Peace Treaty was signed, and Byrnhald recalled all its squads. But soon after, we were attacked by unknown forces.
It was later confirmed to be the Dark Mist Legion of Byrnhald.Their leader Denvel had refused the recall order.

30010803.Content:
To Jenny and Camille:
By the time you see this letter, I will have left this world forever. I'm sorry for leaving without saying goodbye.
But I had no choice.
Jenny, you used to be such a cheerful dreamer. I never believed in any so-called dreamland at the time. But under your hopeful influence, I felt empowered every day. However, after you were injured, it felt like you became someone else. I wanted to carry on your dream, Jenny. Even though you always told me not to be bothered with it, I decided to set off alone in search of the perfect land.

But the voyage changed my perspective. When I started to really observe the world around me, I realized how much beauty I had missed.
Just as I was about to return home, I saw how cruel the world could be.

Jenny, Camille, do you know? Our home was the perfect dreamland all along.
I had hoped to tell you this in person, but sadly, I no longer have that chance.

Forever loving you both, Eder

30012503.Content:
Distinguished councilors, esteemed colleagues, and fellow citizens,
my name is Eddie Hopson, a proud native of Minsterhorn. Though my roots lie there, I have spent many fulfilling years here in Asterleeds, and over time, I have developed a deep and lasting emotional bond with this land.
It is precisely because of that bond that drives me to make the soil that raised me better.
... (Some pages are too damaged to decipher after being chewed by the dog for too long.)




Page 1 of 5
30012503.ChatName: The first page of the speech script

30012504.Content: Right here-two pages of the speech script got blown onto the roof! Can't reach them... You're my only hope!

30012505.Content:
Before I begin, allow me to mention two heroes of the Asterleeds Independence War-Tina and Olvera.
Their deeds inspired this proposal. What I'm about to say is rooted in their legacy.

During the Asterleeds Independence War, we gave our all to resist the Byrnhald forces, despite being vastly outnumbered.
And none shone brighter than these two legends on every battlefield: Tina and Olvera.
It was said that wherever they fought, victory followed.
But it wasn't just their strength.
It was the spirit of Asterleeds they embodied.
Our hunger for freedom. Our unbreakable will. We can see them in the heroes who rose during the war.
That spirit helped us achieve the impossible.




Page: 2/5
30012505.ChatName: The second page of the speech script

30012506.Content:
However, will is a fragile force, shaped and tested by the weight of emotion and reality.
Warriors of Asterleeds draw strength from glimpses of their champions' battlefield valor,
reminding themselves that even foes mightier than themselves can be defeated.

But today, in the prosperity of Asterleeds, that spirit is fading at an alarming rate.




Page: 3/5
30012506.ChatName: The third page of the speech script

30012507.Content:
What have we done since the war ended?
We've drowned ourselves in entertainment. Food District songs are louder than ever.
We praise our progress-the Artisan Guild forging "truth" with every strike.
We trust our strength-thinking Asterleeds Defense Corps soldiers' boots alone will keep enemies away.
But the danger never left. We still depend on Byrnhald for trade.
Behind the celebration lies a hard truth:
We rely too heavily on Byrnhald. If we were to lose them as a trading partner, our markets would suffer greatly.


This looming crisis likely stems from the loss of our wartime spirit. We may appear to be free.
But the Byrnhald's chains still tighten around our necks, unseen yet unbroken.

Now rumors of rising taxes shake the streets.
The fact that one mere whisper has caused such panic? This absurdity is nothing but a warning.




Page: 4/5
30012507.ChatName: The fourth page of the speech script

30012508.Content:
(A grimy medal, judging by its size, likely hung around livestock's neck.
Long neglected, now rusted beyond recognition.
Engraved with a few lines of words.)


Awarded to Billy for Most Majestic Horns during Livestock Division Champion of
the 11th Annual Pastoral Championship
-Raised by the Hobson Family

30012509.Content:
Wake up, Asterians!
The spirit of the Asterleeds Independence War may have faded, but it's not gone entirely.
As long as we're willing to face the truth, there's still a chance to rebuild our confidence.
From a young age, I was taught: "Start with small things."
So here is my proposal-Let's develop animal husbandry! Let's stop letting Byrnhald hold us hostage over food.
Not so long ago, the domesticated Caprahorns of Minsterhorn once won the agricultural championship.
The Caprahorns that roam the Asteria Plains are our natural advantage.

Of course, livestock farming is just the beginning. But it might be the right place to start.
I'm just an ordinary citizen. And this is what I see, and what I hope to change.

Apologies for taking up your time, esteemed councilors. Please allow my proposal to linger in your minds for just a little while.
Perhaps it will stir some thought, or perhaps it will simply fade away.
I'm Eddie Hopson from Minsterhorn, and I'd be honored to do something for Asterleeds.

30012702.Content:
The Gigantic Automaton, ancient and formidable creations forged by the Bapharians, were pivotal during the war against the dragons.
According to legend, these colossal machines were not reclaimed by the Divine, but rather, scattered and lost throughout the corners of the Continent of Magna.
The Divine's texts reveal that each Gigantic Automaton can only be activated by a chosen user.

30013904.Content:
The Ruins of Andra City, once ruled by the Bapharian Divines, now lie before me, an awe-inspiring sight.
How magnificent, how exhilarating!
The records in the Bapharian Creed's doctrine didn't exaggerate. This is, without a doubt, a masterpiece left behind by the Bapharian Divines.
The Artisanship in this ring-shaped device is beyond belief-it defies the natural laws in ways I cannot comprehend.
It's truly a work of the divine. The Divine' creations surpass all imagination. I long to see more.
Too many unsolved mysteries surround the Divine's existence-perhaps this journey will unveil some of their secrets. If so, my life will not have been lived in vain!

30013906.Content: (It seems Fido's sensed something once again. Let's follow it and see what it's found.)

30013908.Content: (It seems that Fido has sensed hostility?!)

30013909.Content: (Next, let's see what Fido has discovered.)

30013910.Content:
Strange.
Very strange.
This city-once so powerful-has been reduced to ruin.
The destruction is clear. The damage to these homes is unmistakably the result of war.
How could a city under the protection of the Divine fall to such devastation?
Was there an enemy more powerful than the Bapharian Divines?
No... that's impossible.
The truth must lie beyond what is apparent, and I am determined to uncover it.

30013914.Content: (Great. That's the third one now... and still, no sign of Grace.)

30013915.Content:
So that's the truth... After reading the records inscribed in these ancient scrolls, everything makes sense now.
No wonder Void Mist plagues this place-no wonder even a mighty city-state ruled by the Divine fell.
Their prosperity... it was built on something too disturbing to name...
if this knowledge is real-then what will become of our world? I can't bring myself to think further...
But it's too late to take any of this back. The Void Mist coils around me now...
Still... perhaps it's better this way. My thirst for truth is quenched. As for the future... I no longer wish to see it. I'm tired. Let me rest.

30013917.Content: (Why is he running? It's dangerous here. I have to bring Fido back.)

30013919.Content: (It's Grace. He's... he's been eroded by the Void Corruption.)

30013920.Content: The truth... such a terrible truth!

30013923.Content: (Poor Fido... I have to return. I have to tell Sandro what happened)

30015106.Content: Alright, done! Let's go back and find Kobo!

30015201.Content:
A distant whirlpool had begun pulling the ship into its spiral grip.
Several cargo holds were punctured by jagged reefs beneath the surface.
Though we managed to pitch up the breached sections, most of the cloth cargo sustained irreversible water damage...

The captain tried to reassure us: once we passed through this treacherous basin, the journey would be safe.

But what are our true odds against these murderous currents?
Outside, the wind howls. The Merchant Guild scrambles to assess the mounting losses.
According to prior agreements, this disaster will likely spark serious disputes...

All we can do now is pray-to escape this sea alive.

30015202.Content:
The mast has been shattered!
Fights have broken out among some crew members over fresh water-desperation has turned them into predators, eyes gleaming like starving wolves.
...
(Several lines are obscured by ink)
...
The cargo hold's barrier has burst again. Even now, the Merchant Guild is debating how to salvage what remains...
But the hull continues to groan and tremble, dragged mercilessly toward the heart of the vortex. Can we ever survive it?

30015203.Content:
Our food is nearly gone.
The freighter is inching ever closer to the center of the maelstrom...
It feels like escape is no longer an option.
I thought I saw a flicker of light deep within the whirlpool's core. Maybe it was only my mind playing tricks in despair...

If anyone finds this letter-please, carry my final blessings to my family.

Forever yours...
(The rest of the writing is water-damaged beyond recognition)

30015302.Content:
Dear little Aiden,
By the time you open this letter, I should have already left Minsterhorn,
and you should have grown into a young man capable of protecting yourself, right?

The truth is, your brother isn't going on a grand adventure.
I've contracted a rare illness, and there's no good treatment for it right now.
I didn't want you and parents to see me taking medicine, so I've been hiding it from you all.

You're a grown-up now, you can protect yourself and our parents.
I heard there's a secret remedy that can cure diseases somewhere in the north, and that's the purpose of my journey.

But don't worry about me. I'll come back as soon as I'm cured.
Until then, you must take care of Mom and Dad for me, and protect our home.
I've buried a gift for you under the tree next to our house. Remember to go get it.

May the Time Locket protect you.

Isa

30016001.Content: Damn it, the device activated suddenly! The delayed timer must have triggered it...

30016002.Content: Adventurers, I think I smell a monster! Please-protect me!

30020102.Content: (The scholar from earlier has vanished. We should head back to the camp and investigate.)

30020201.Content: We're close. It should be just up ahead.

30020202.Content: Looks like someone's over there. Adventurers, let's check it out.

30020401.Content: (I've already asked everyone I could find... I guess all that's left is to take Airona's advice and try my luck at the Pioneer Bureau.)

30020402.Content: (A footprint. Still fresh. Someone passed through here recently.)

30020403.Content: (The scuffed ground suggests a conflict occurred. Footsteps trail in all directions, long strides as though they were fleeing.)

30020501.Content: (Looks like a fading shoe print-left here long ago.)

30020502.Content: (Some burn marks-signs they camped here for a while. Let's have a look around.)

30020503.Content: (Strange. Seems there's something buried beneath this stone...)

30020504.Content:
...
Not the right time yet. Damn Swindler. That bastard's really good at hiding who he is.
The problem is, we don't have enough evidence to bring him down yet. All we need is proof that he rented my boat that day. That's it. Until then, we can't report him-God knows how many of his people are in the Corps or even on the Council.
I can't believe I was stupid enough to fall for his act. Just because he offered a little extra cash, I let him use the boat without even signing a contract.
...
And now... Mom's illness is getting worse. She can't even speak clearly anymore. This damn accusation of treason has ruined everything. I can't be an adventurer. I can't even go back to my old job!
I need money. A lot of it.
...
There's really no other way. The forest survey team is hiring guides. It'll take a week to make what I need for Mom's treatment. I know that area well. This might be my last shot.
Carter keeps trying to talk me out of it. Says it's too dangerous. He's not wrong-if it wasn't, the reward wouldn't be so high.
Before I left, I gave all the evidence I had to my best buddy Carter. I told him, if I don't come back... at least I don't want people calling me a traitor. I'm not. I'm not!
...
We set off. So far, it's gone pretty smoothly.
The team has vast experience, they aren't called the survey team for nothing. The route the ecologists picked helped us avoid almost all the monsters. Amazing.
There's this guy, Lyon (I think that's his name?), who joined last minute like me. He keeps accidentally attracting monsters. The captain already chewed him out once.
...
Now the wind's starting to pick up. It's been dark all day. If it starts pouring, we're in trouble. We lit a fire to keep the monsters away-windy nights always stir them up.
Luckily, there's a camp nearby. The team's got multiple overnight spots set up in the valley just for this kind of weather. We're crashing here tonight.

30020505.Content:
(The text above has been soaked and is no longer legible.)
...
We are stuck. According to meteorological patterns, this wind doesn't seem natural. The team's ecologist suspects it's the work of goblins.
Dark clouds have begun to form in the distance, rolling in from the sea. That's not a good sign. If the goblins are up to some weird ritual and it clashes with the seasonal storms, things could get really bad...
The monsters' howls echo from all directions. I'm glad we've already altered our route. There are still some supplies left at Station No. 6. It's on high ground, so it won't flood. We can hide there for a while.

...

The young guy traveling with us, named Roy, has gone missing.

...

Everyone's doing their best, but the wind now is strong enough to snap trees. The team can barely communicate. If we don't return to Station No. 6 soon, things will get trickier.
We found his backpack near a tree by the cliff, along with some messy footprints. Lyon guessed he might've slipped and fallen. Let's hope he survives.
No one really knows where Roy came from. He wasn't a formally registered adventurer. Other than erecting a cenotaph by the tree outside the station, there isn't much we can do.

...

The storm is coming...

30020506.Content: (No further clues here. But Carter seems to know more than he's letting on-let's circle back and question him in Port Town.)

30020701.Content: I know where he is. Swindler usually hides by the beach at this hour.

30020702.Content: The mastermind is still at large, and the people are suffering... I've failed them as Council Chair.

30020703.Content: Don't let Swindler get away! He's trying to escape by yacht!

30020704.Content: I'll leave this to you I'm going after him!

30020705.Content: (They're running toward the docks... I have to help Carter...)

30020801.Content:
Thank goodness there were other adventurers around to help me out. Without them, I wouldn't have made it into Everfall Forest at all.
The air's really damp tonight. It feels like it might rain later. I can't stay out in the open for too long. I need to find a place to camp soon.
Honestly, right now I just want to curl up somewhere and eat Mom's stew...
Sander is licking my hand nonstop. You're thirsty too, huh? Let's find some water and give you a bath too.
I've got 2 pieces of bread left and a moonfruit another adventurer gave me. Should be enough to get through the night. I'll look for more food tomorrow.
... (The writing gets hard to read here-it's smudged and messy.)
We should keep moving for...
(The page is torn off after this point.)

30020802.Content:
I want to go home. I want to go home. I want to go home. I want to go home!
There are monsters everywhere! My leg still hurts from the scratches. I just want Mom's cooking... I just want to sleep in my warm bed with Sander!
Why can't I find the exit?! Why?!

30020803.Content:
If anyone finds this, please help me. I don't know where I am. I'm surrounded by ruins.
A monster attacked us and I got hurt-I can't walk anymore...
I managed to crawl into a crevice between the ruins and the valley to hide... but I know it's only a matter of time before I'm discovered...
I gave this letter to Sander and told it to find someone-anyone-who could help...
If you're reading this... please save me...

30020804.Content:
I couldn't find a camp. No water, no food. Not even fruit. And weirdly, not a single monster either.
According to adventurers outside, the monsters in Everfall Forest are far more ferocious, but I haven't seen any, just a few wild rabbits running around.
The forest is way too quiet at night... it's actually kinda scary. Thank god Sander's with me.
Still, thinking about that thing being out there... gives me a weird burst of energy!
...
If I can find it and give it to Aishe, she'll definitely agree to watch the fireworks at Asterleeds Beach with me! You bet!
Sander's already dozed off next to me. I should rest too-save my strength for tomorrow. Still need to find food, water, and then head deeper in the search of that thing...
...
I could've sworn I heard something just now. Maybe I'm just overtired...
There are some ruins up the hill to the east... Maybe I can find something useful there.
Maybe that thing is...
(The rest of the writing is smudged-probably slobbered on by Sander.)

30020805.Content:
Mom, I'm sorry. I don't think I can make it back...
The wounds on my body have begun to fester, but strangely, I don't feel any pain. Perhaps a small mercy in this grim situation.
There's no food in my backpack. I didn't want Sander to die here with me, so I sent it ahead with a message for help...
I know no one will ever come to a place like this. I should've listened to you and stayed home...
Mom, I'm sorry. I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry...
...
Mom, you probably will never read this...
If anyone finds this letter, could you please do me a favor?
There are two of my diaries buried under a tree in Minsterhorn. Please deliver the red one to Ms. Mary in town, and the white one to Aishe near the shop...
...
Maybe now... I can finally rest...
...
May love stay in this world forever...
Yael

30020806.Content:
I was awakened by the rain. I thought I'd reached heaven, but I was still in this hell.
Suddenly I saw the bracelet Mom made for me slide out of my backpack. Sadness instantly jolted me back to clarity.
I realized I can't die here yet...
Sander has been gone a long time. It must have reached somewhere safe by now. I have to hold on until the rescuers arrive.
But I have no food or water. I saw smoke rising in the north. Maybe there's a camp there.
My wounds seem to be starting to heal a little. I hope the last of the bandages in my backpack can get me that far...
...
Yes! I can do this! Mom! Wait for me!
And Ai...
(The paper is too torn and the writing below is no longer visible.)

30021001.Content: Next up is the second Control Panel.

30021002.Content: Then the third. Pay attention to how I tell you to operate it.

30021003.Content:
Hills,
By the time you read this, I might already be taken by the Creed's enforcers or the duchy's military police.
I've hidden all my research in the usual place.
You once told me I should give up-that nothing good comes from going against the Creed. But once the edict was issued, I knew I was right to push forward.
You're probably calling me stubborn again...
Perhaps I am wrong, but as we both know, only history will deliver the final verdict on us. What scares me more than being wrong is
how history suddenly comes to an abrupt halt at a certain point-as if all that came before had ceased to exist.
Hills, I truly believe: if you don't know where you come from, you'll never know where you're going.
If you're willing to keep going, take my research to Asterleeds. Maybe the Ruins of Andra City on the Asteria Plains still bear echoes of a lost civilization.
But if you can't... I get it. This road is hard. Maybe too hard. If that's the case, just forget this letter.
Looking back, I think my happiest moments were those quiet afternoons at the institute, sorting through dusty documents with you.
All the best.
-Azik

From this moment on, our people will sever all ties with the surface. I fear we may never cross paths again.

Outsiders aren't the monsters we were told they were....

30030019.Content:
The brilliance of the past lies quietly among the ruins.

The Continent of Magna is steeped in history, once home to civilizations that glittered like the stars.

To rediscover the glory and wisdom of these lost worlds, we, a team of elite scholars from every field, are preparing for a groundbreaking expedition, combining rigorous research and cutting-edge methods to explore and interpret ancient ruins.



Recruitment Categories:

Scholars (Filled)
Historians, ecologists, ancient language specialists, etc.

Craftsmen (Filled)
Experts in heritage preservation, excavation, and equipment support.

Adventurers (Urgently Needed!!!)
Dangerous monsters still lurk in the canyon. We need skilled survivors and seasoned fighters.
You'll escort scholars, help set up camps, and support site investigations.

Archivists (Filled)
Manage data, maintain equipment, and organize records. Some survival skills required.
Bonus if you can cook!


How to Join: Head to the first floor of Ocean Hill and speak with Mr. Smith, the expedition leader.
Merchants with funds not accepted.
Frio School applicants will be turned away.

Because now we know ■■■ is incredibly dangerous...

If you can't handle it, you might end up like Lia...
Am I really just going to sit by and watch my kin die, one by one?
Is this power truly worth the price?

30040807.Content:
Chapter 6.3: Origins of the Webber Energy Network

The lead artisan was named 'Webber'.
Although the use of relics was limited at the time, Webber was determined to design an energy network system for the city.

The idea was bold and forward-thinking—by integrating the energy network from the very start of construction, he laid a solid foundation for the widespread use of relics in present-day Asterleeds.
Today in Asterleeds, everything from cooking appliances in wealthy households to ventilation systems in restaurants...
even lighting and signage infrastructure all rely on the energy network designed by Webber to function properly.

To honor the dedication of these artisans and Webber's visionary work,
Asterleeds's energy system was officially renamed 'Webber'.
This admirable group of artisans became known as the unique Artitects, and many remain active within the Artisan Guild to this day.
