Alician calendar, June 19, Year ■■■

The great pirate, Heathcliff Stormwrath, is now buried at sea.
Now, there is only Orlando the cobbler.
Facing the sea breeze of Asterleeds.
Repenting.

Greed was our downfall. We could have had a bright future.
Aria, Gwen, Lorian... all buried at sea.
We originally gathered for this jewel,
yet we were torn apart because of it...
As a captain, I was useless.
Couldn't secure the jewel nor protect my companions...

A pirate's honor has faded away with the past.
I hope the fleet never finds me.

Alician calendar, June 18, Year ■■■

The sun in Asterleeds is warm.
But there are some dark corners that even the warmest sunlight cannot reach.
Even after so many years, with a new family, a new identity.
Those events are still etched in my mind.
Like the curse on the Abyssal Eye, it follows me like a shadow.
Always at the most difficult, most critical moments...
It lands the fatal blow.

Alician calendar, June 17, Year ■■■
It's that time again.
Every year on these few days, I have that dream.
I always return to that cave.
I relive climbing to the highest reef in the cave,
drifting with the current for a whole day, pecked by vultures until I was a ■ mess.
I was clearly prepared to meet my friends,
but was rescued just before sunset...
There is no more terrifying dream than this, none.

30051002.Content: There are too many monsters here, Adventurer... Let's reduce their numbers first.

30051003.Content: Adventurer, look at that crack in the rock over there. Is there a piece of paper stuck inside?

30051004.Content:
Month of Storms, Day 18

I've decided to take a gamble!
I've got nothing left to lose anyway...
The worst that can happen is I lose my life! Bring it on!
Who the ■■ wants to feed the skyfish in this stinking cave!
I'm going for it!

30051005.Content:
Month of Storms, Day 16

From what I've observed, above the dome of this cave is just dark seawater.
And the highest reef seems to pierce through this sac cave.
This is unbelievable. I have no idea who built this darn place.

Month of Storms, Day 17

If I climb up this reef, will I end up in the sea?
And if I get into the sea, can I swim to a place with ships?
Honestly, even for someone as tough as me, I don't know if I can succeed.
But, rather than dying in this stinking deep-sea cave and feeding the skyfish,
I'd much rather see what strange sight lies above this sac cave.

30051006.Content:
(A rusty dagger. A few words are faintly visible on the finely forged blade.)
"Heathcliff Stormwrath"
(Several other words are etched on the reverse side.)
"A nobleman's robes are full of maggots."
(At the base of the dagger is an exquisite skull.)

30051007.Content:
Month of Storms, Day 15
Those brats like Aria are usually as timid as mice.
But when it came down to it, they risked their lives to cover for me!
Why is that?!
Why!! Why am I the one who survived!!

Month of Storms, Day 16
Caught some skyfish to eat.
I've finally made it through!
■■■■ it!!

Forget it!! All that depressing crap I carved on theeastern reef before!
Man-eating monster lizards! Stinking giant skyfish!
And the ■■ Abyssal Eye!
To ■■ with all of you!
I'm gonna live! I'm gonna live! I'm gonna live!

30051008.Content: Found it! Adventurer, come look! There's a passage etched here!

30051009.Content:
To those who seek the Abyssal Eye! Heed my words!
The great pirate Heathcliff briefly possessed it.

But even with my status, I couldn't suppress its evil power!
First, the ship was wrecked, and we fell into this underwater sac cave.
Then the monsters of the deep were drawn to it!
My crew, my treasure, all swallowed whole...

Avenge me and finish what I could not!
If you can slay that sea monster, the jewel is yours.

(Below is a roughly drawn map, with a dotted line ending in an X.)
The monster's lair
To summon it, you need the heavy scent of many skyfish.
Don't ask me how I know. I don't want to relive my failed revenge.

30051010.Content: What was that sound... Be careful!

30051017.Content: This is bad... Get out of the way!

30051101.Content: (This should do it... Next is brine.)

30051102.Content: Who would collect brine alone in such a dangerous place? Well, the quality seems good.

30051104.Content: But don't get cocky. Soon, you'll see what we're really capable of.

30051601.Content: (Hmm... is this cobalt liquid from when the workers were cutting the anemones?)

30051602.Content: (Oh no... It must be this liquid that's affecting my mind.)

30051603.Content: (I need to find a way to break free from its control!)

30051604.Content: Strange, the Anemone Workers seem to be coming to their senses too.

30051605.Content: (The Anemone Workers here seem quite normal. Let's ask if they've encountered any anemone Anomalys.)

30051702.Content: (Hmm... there are this many? I should go ask Dorunik)

30051703.Content: (There they are! Those few were Ereka's underlings last time)

30051704.Content: (I'd better find a place to eavesdrop on what they're up to...)

30051705.Content: (This spot works. Just need to drive off the nearby monsters first...)

30052101.Content:
(A hide scroll made of Skyfish skin, with a few crudely scrawled lines on it)
"Hey! Whoever stole my brine, I'm coming to settle the score!
Last time I lost because I wasn't at my best and couldn't give it my all!
But now I've found a way to definitely beat you!
I challenge you to a rematch at the third reef south of the cave!
So what do you say? Got the guts to show up?!

If you're too scared...
Just pickle yourself and feed yourself to the Skyfish. Save me the trouble of tracking you down!"

-Wilbert
(At the bottom is a doodle of a little stick figure being stabbed with a dagger. The figure's eyes are drawn as two X's.)

30052102.Content: Boss! Someone's coming! Is it the one?!

30052103.Content: I thought someone wouldn't show up. Get ready to welcome our guest, boys!

30052104.Content: So, can you smell that new scent in the air?

30052105.Content: It might be hard to tell the first time... but the scent of wounds is always the clearest.

30052106.Content: Keep sniffing! You'll soon know exactly where they are...

30052107.Content: Ugh... this is a bit awkward. These monsters stink so much they're messing up the scent.

30052108.Content: Clear out a few before moving forward!

30052109.Content: Alright, now we can keep moving.

30052110.Content: Look, those people over there seem to be talking about something...

30052111.Content: Whoa, they actually hid their secret base here? Pretty clever...

30052112.Content: That pungent smell in the air... No doubt they're hiding brine kegs inside.

30052113.Content: Adventurer, let's split up and search. We might find clues to reveal their true purpose.

30052114.Content:
Act One: Dirge of Fate in the Rusted Iron Coffin

Oh! This iron coffin kissed by the Abyssal (Note: refers to a secure wooden crate) has spat out a piece of parchment!
"Sulfurfire dances with the salt crystals, and the abyssal gate shall kneel to the madman."
What a magnificent opening verse!
Wilbert's trembling growl is more moving than the wails of a seagull:
"Captain, this must be Heathcliff Stormwrath's love letter to destiny!"
Let the parasites keep sneering!
When my brine bombs sound their overture,
their hypocrisy will be shattered with the coral throne!
(Wildly scrawled note: Wilbert suggested stuffing the explosives in pickled fish kegs. He has been punished to lick barnacles off the mast.)
30052114.ChatName: Captain Livera's One-Act Play Notes Part I

30052115.Content:
Act Three: Duet of Salt and Scabs

Third time! The third time! The crystals betrayed me again at the final moment!
(Smashes the flask, and glass shards scatter like applause after a show)
The salt grains cured in tidal brine were meant to ignite the fire of chaos, yet they've turned into sticky poison!
(Lifts a failed batch with the tip of a sword)
Look! This blue curse bore pearls in Ereka's hands...
(Suddenly lowers voice)
Maybe I should sell this to one of those noble Asterleeds ladies?
Title: Let The Ashes of Your Enemies Nourish Your Beauty...
No! My ambition shall never be reduced to some landlubber's beauty ad!
30052115.ChatName: Captain Livera's One-Act Play Notes Part II

30052116.Content:
Act Five: Satirical Interlude of the Dove and the Brine Keg

Miss Ereka's spies are more annoying than a shark's gums!
(Draws an eyepatch-wearing dove with wine stains)
Ereka actually dreams of wrapping every pirate fang in a white flag!
After she took over, Ereka made some "Seafaring Pact" with that fool Raoul.
"No attacking landfolk proactively."
Come on, pirates without violence are like rain without wet! Absurd!
She must've forgotten what being a pirate means.
And she's forgotten why we came here in the first place.
We came to this cave to find the legendary Siren's Tear.
And now? It's just her private stash!
30052116.ChatName: Captain Livera's One-Act Play Notes Part III

30052117.Content:
Final Chapter: Solo Encore of the Blue Flame

It's done! It's done! (scrawled handwriting)
When the compressed salt block burst into ghostly blue flames,
all the Skyfish in the cave leaped into a waltz of escape!
A deep crater was blasted into the reef in the cave!
Thus, the mission to search for Siren's Tear is within reach!

What's the big deal if Wilbert's dentures flew off?
By this time tomorrow, the legendary Siren's Tear will bring me an entire fleet!

(A spotlight shines on Asterleeds.
The background echoes with the roar of 37 ceremonial cannons.
Ereka's white-flag ship turns to confetti on cue)

-The End-
30052117.ChatName: Captain Livera's One-Act Play Notes Part IV

30060201.Content: (Hmm... These unique footprints... They seems to belong to Goblins.)

30060203.Content: (Looks like the blasted "thief" escaped by climbing over this cliff face.)

30060204.Content: Hey, Adventurer! Hey, over here, over here!

30060205.Content: How despicable, to climb in from here.

30060206.Content: A-adventurer! Quick! That nasty goblin just appeared!

30070201.Content: Adventurer, look! Over there, that person is exhausted and sitting on the ground.

30070202.Content: There are too many Goblins nearby. Adventurer, you'll have to take out some monsters to get close to him.

30070203.Content: (Hmm, this should be close enough to him now.)

30070204.Content: What a wonderful scent... Adventurer, the Muku shouldn't attack you now. Go on.

30070205.Content: Excellent, the perfume is working. Now, try to make friendly contact with them.

30070301.Content:
Have you ever noticed those travelers known as Scavengers?
They refuse to be bound by the mundane world, wandering freely like the wind.
They carry their entire belongings in bulging packs,
hurrying through alleys and vanishing quietly into the crowds.
Their lives are like fallen leaves drifting in the wind,
brushing past the world, free yet lonely.

My name is Zeke, and I'm journeying across the continent of Regnus as a scavenger.
After a long trek, my companions and I finally arrived at the Asteria Plains.
We heard of a mysterious forest there called the Duskdye Woods .
We wanted to explore it while visiting some fellow scavenger friends who live there.
However, that forest is full of dangers, with monsters roaming and Brigands lurking.

For safety's sake, I'm now recruiting a brave adventurer to escort us.
If you're interested, find the man with a giant backpack named Zeke near the Pioneer Bureau.
The contact phrase: "Hey Zeke, found any treasures today?"

Rest assured, the reward will be ample.

30070303.Content: Look, still as many monsters as ever...

30070304.Content: Time for adventurers to shine! Please clear out some of these monsters for us.

30070305.Content: Yeah, so we can sneak past along the edge... See you in a bit!

30070307.Content: Whoa... This path is so narrow. It's a bit scary.

30070308.Content: If you're that scared, we shouldn't have come this way to begin with.

30070401.Content: Mission complete! You're looking much younger now!

30070402.Content: But remember-the effect is time-limited, so we'd better move quickly.

30070403.Content: I'll stay hidden nearby to keep watch while you investigate.

30070404.Content: Hey, you're walking too much like an adult... Imagine how a child walks.

30070405.Content: I can't seem to hear the detective's voice anymore. Did I go too far...

30070406.Content: Where... where am I... Was I attacked by the culprit?

30070407.Content: Damn it... I can't remember that person's face at all... Whatever, I need to save the child first!

30070501.Content: (I don't see any Crimson mushroom. Wait... what's that?)

30070502.Content: (Looks like it stopped breathing a while ago. Could it be related to the Crimson mushroom?)

30070503.Content: (Damn... I think I've angered a monster!)

30070802.Content: I didn't expect this. An adventurer. It seems my luck has turned.

30070805.Content: Why aren't you panicking at all? Don't you want to catch that Brazer member anymore?

30070806.Content: Because we already anticipated this... Just wait and enjoy the show.

30215001.Content: Adventurer, be careful! Don't startle the Goblin leader.

30215002.Content: See, it's fine. The Adventurer has already passed. Let's follow.

30215005.Content: Muku and Goblins here are fighting even more fiercely.

30215006.Content: Yeah... They're much more savage than before. I really don't know why.

30215007.Content: Isn't it better if they fight? Look, we can use this chance to slip past.

30215009.Content: There seem to be fewer monsters here.

30215010.Content: Don't let your guard down. There are many slopes near the camp. Watch out for ambushes.

30215011.Content: We should reach it by going up this slope. Hang in there!

30216001.Content: Hmm... This spot is good. Looks like a path monsters must take.

30216002.Content: This place is a bit remote, but it can provide early warning against some treacherous monsters.

30216003.Content: This position... Alright, let's give it a try.

30217001.Content: Strange, why is there nothing here?

30217002.Content: Found it, here! Adventurer! Come here!

30303001.Content: The animals here all seem uneasy as if they harbor some hatred toward humans.

30303002.Content: I need to find one and talk to it to figure out what's going on.

30311001.Content: Okay, we're clear to investigate. Let's search nearby for the stolen goods.

30311002.Content: (What's this? Uneaten rations? Guess the demi-humans didn't like them.)

30311003.Content: (Looks like a camp water bottle. Goblins turned it into a toy.)

30311004.Content: (That cooking pot's gone too, stolen by goblins.)

30312001.Content: Over here, adventurer! Look at the cliff. See those flowers?

30312002.Content: Check out the Boarriers. Those Crimson Vesicles might be on them.

30312003.Content: Please help me, adventurer. I'm useless in a fight.

30315001.Content: The scouts say the demi-humans are clustered in three locations. Let's go one by one.

30315002.Content: Lots of goblins here... Let's get to work, warriors.

30315003.Content: Plenty of demi-humans too... Your move, adventurer.

30315004.Content: (These ones are tougher than the ones outside... What is that?)

30315005.Content: This is the last spot... We're almost there, adventurer.

30316004.Content:
Dear Ereka,

Greetings to you.
Victoria is a remarkably clever child. No one knows where she came from. I discovered her while delivering documents to the Corps. She was delirious from hunger, so I brought her home. She has stayed with me ever since.
She excels at solving puzzles. She requested I include these details in my letter. While I don't understand their purpose, she insisted they would help you, so I've included them.
She claims she can locate you. While I don't understand how she'll manage this feat, I recognize that even if she finds you, I might not be able to bring you back to the Duchy.
Nevertheless, I maintain hope that she will find you.
The day you were taken to sea, Hugues and I commandeered a fisherman's boat, but Duchy soldiers discovered us shortly after we set sail.
Some claim raiders took you aboard their ship, while others insist you perished.
Though this may now sound like excuses for my helplessness and inaction, Ereka, even without knowing the complete situation, I have always stood ready to be your companion. Or your accomplice.

Perhaps you've forgotten, but before your departure, you scattered nuts across the yard to feed those rarely-seen birds. The remaining seeds took root in the soil and astonishingly developed into beautiful vining plants bearing new fruit.
I've included one of these fruits with this letter.
Should you receive it, it will serve as my eyes.

Hoping to return to your side,
Lloyd

30320002.Content: (Doesn't look any different... Let's find someone to ask where this "Iron Gauntlet" is.)

30413001.Content:
Step 1: Play music (consider having Pipewater do it, other musicians are too expensive).
Step 2: Eulogy (to be performed by Benedict).
Step 3: Moment of silence (to be observed by all).
Step 4: Knock on the nearby pipe walls to clear the passage.
Step 5: Send the deceased into the sewage pipe (to be performed by Mortimer).

May the deceased rest in peace. Glory to Webber.
30413001.ChatName: Underground Funeral Plan for Lady Chrissie

30413002.Content: (Hmm, looks like everything's in order. I'll head back to Benedict.)

30570003.Content: Is anyone here? Excuse me, I was sent by the Asterleeds Defense Corps...

30570004.Content: Huh? There seems to be a note stuck on the door.

30570005.Content: Gone to Minsterhorn for supplies, not at home for now. -The Ramsys

30601001.Content:
My friend, by the time you hear this message,
I'll have already left the surface with the last of our kin.
Too much time has slipped away. I had no other choice...
From now on, our people will sever all contact with the surface. It's likely we'll never meet again.

There have always been differences between our races.
But after meeting you, I came to realize those from other races aren't as unreasonable as they say.
And those of the same race aren't always as trustworthy as they seem.
Forgive my silent departure. I just couldn't bring myself to say goodbye.
The time we shared meant the world to me.
To me, it was a balm that soothed every wound.

To honor our bond, I've left behind something special.
It's in the secure vault at the deepest part of the facility.
Until you arrive, a Golem will keep it safe.
It's a treasure meant only for you.

This is the last thing I can do before leaving.

Right now, I'm overwhelmed with emotions.
I no longer know what else to say.
All I can do is express myself this way.
Once this message ends, the vault will open.
Take care, my human friend.

30601003.Content: We'll hold them off. You go rescue Destinee.

30601004.Content: You're really persistent. Fine, I'll deal with you later!

30603001.Content: This seems to be a demi-human habitat.

30603002.Content: Could Mode 1 be demi-humans? I need to record this.

30603003.Content: Adventurer, please get rid of some of the demi-humans so I can record a sample of the mode change.

30603004.Content: It seems the signal is pointing to the cliff of this mountain.

30603005.Content: Adventurer, please go up and take a look. I'll wait for you on the flat ground above.

30603006.Content: (This actually looks like an Imagine Seed, doesn't it?)

30603007.Content: Strange, this is clearly a hidden spot behind some green leaves...

30603008.Content: Adventurer, please go over and take a look. I'll stay here and continue to record the mode changes.

30603009.Content: Aaaah, there's something so terrifying hidden here?

30604001.Content: Grab my hand-just like we did when we came here.

30604002.Content: I'm never using this thing to cross a canyon ever again!!!

30604004.Content:
Day 1
Entered Windhowl Canyon with the scholar group. The terrain is treacherous.
Began exploring the nearby rock formations.

Day 5
Finished surveying the nearby terrain. Preparing to start the survey of the floating islands.
There are plenty of floating islands, but the leader says he never thought about how to get on them?
The people from the Artisan Guild can't help either. What kind of group did I join?

Day 6
The dry rations taste bad, there are sounds of demi-humans all around, and the bed is lumpy...
Smith, oh Smith, you've got the brains of a Caprahorn!
How could you put all the funds into recruitment? Logistics are important too!

Day 7
No progress.
The other group is using a Legacy to traverse the mountain ravines. I'm so jealous.

Day 8
No progress.

Day 9
No progress.

Day 10
No progress.

Day 11
Floating Island Survey Report...

30605002.Content: I can't believe there's still an active defense module in this canyon! It's incredible!

30606001.Content: It seems the drift of the gravel has shifted to the right.

30606002.Content: Wow, why is there a pile of monsters? Adventurer, help me!

30607001.Content: Get away from me, you disgusting monsters!

30607002.Content: (That sounds like a person's voice. I should see what's going on.)

30607003.Content: Sigh, I finally found it, but it's so high up. What am I supposed to do now?

30608001.Content: (There's a strange ore near the stopping point... Could that be the reason?)

30608002.Content: (The area is covered with strange symbiotic fungi... Could that be the reason?)

30608003.Content: (This... looks like a fragment of a ruin. Could that be why?)

30608004.Content: There are too many monsters. It's impossible to start setting up the Legacy... Let's clear some of them out first, Adventurer.

30608005.Content: There are a lot of monsters around here too... Please, Adventurer.

30609001.Content: No, that spot has too little cover and is easily exposed. Let's keep looking.

30609002.Content: Not feasible. There are too many monsters nearby, it's easy to get distracted. Let's look elsewhere.

30609003.Content: Hmm, this spot is quite suitable, but it's a bit small. If there's nothing better, this will have to do.

30609004.Content: It's a hidden arrow... Crap! Get down! We've been ambushed!!

30609007.Content: (Sounds like someone inside is yelling for help? I should go in and see what's happening.)

30610001.Content: It's a key! What could this key open?

30610003.Content: Adventurer, thank you for your kindness, but my grandmother always told me that the law of life is equal exchange. Since you didn't choose one of my items, I will give you a gift as well.
30610003.ChatName: A small note left by Janice

30610004.Content: It can't be such a coincidence.....

30610005.Content: Was the key I picked up earlier for this box?

30610006.Content:
Adventurer, I obtained these bird feathers during a hunt. Our people use them to decorate masks for festivals, representing the fearless spirit of our warriors in the hunt.
I give them to you, hoping that courage will always accompany you on your adventures.
30610006.ChatName: A small note left by Janice

30610007.Content:
Adventurer, I obtained these Caprahorns during a hunt. Our people always use them to make parts for musical instruments.
I give them to you, hoping that music be your companion on your journey and bring you the blessings of our ancestors.
30610007.ChatName: A small note left by Janice

30610008.Content:
Adventurer, this is the mineral I found by chance on my travels. The land is always like this, giving us unexpected gifts.
I give them to you. I hope every part of your journey is blessed by the land, and I wish you reach your true homestead.
30610008.ChatName: A small note left by Janice

30611001.Content: The view from up here is great.

30611002.Content: Oops, sorry, I almost bumped into you. What are you doing crouching here?

50050001.Content: (I've gathered a significant amount of information. Let me use the Anchor Notes to piece the clues together.)

50050002.Content: Bertram is my priority-I can't let him slip away in the chaos. You handle the others, adventurers.

50050003.Content: (Based on everything I've deduced, three suspects stand out.)

50080001.Content: Observe carefully, he will hide in the Void Engram!

50080002.Content: I just like Void Engram, is that wrong too?

50080003.Content: You simply cannot understand. I am pursuing the ultimate dark aesthetic!

50080004.Content: Sigh, stop fighting. Isn't it good to experience the art of Void Engram together?

50080005.Content: Forget it... For me to perish together with my beloved Void Mist... is also a romantic ending...

50090001.Content: Out of my way! Kill those two-now!

50090003.Content: Let me go, and I'll make it worth your while!

50090004.Content: Don't fall for his lies. Seize him!

50090005.Content: Everyone, run! And you two blockheads up ahead-move it!

50090006.Content: Huh? They actually broke free?! <style="emph-gn">{*me.name*}</style>, Don't let them escape!

50090010.Content:
In the 602nd year of the Alician calendar, restrictive measures were imposed upon Tina.

Following the restoration of the Hruga Seal, Tina's continued existence became a subject of grave concern across the The Continent of Magna.
Many councilors believed that, for the sake of continental safety, strict protective measures were necessary-measures that would, in effect, strip Tina of her personal freedom entirely.
Fearing that excessive restrictions might provoke unintended consequences, a compromise was ultimately reached, resulting in Tina's confinement to the Asteria Plains under the direct supervision of Defense Corps Commander Olvera.

Note: Though Olvera and Tina were once close, the Kanamia Forest Skirmish had driven a wedge between them. This strained relationship requires close monitoring for potential operational complications. Should any unforeseen incidents arise, the reinstatement of full containment protocols would need to be reconsidered.

50090011.Content: Lady Airona, long time no see.

50090012.Content: Tavernmaster, do you know a fellow named Colin?

50090013.Content:
In the 608th year of the Alician calendar, the Council once again turned its attention to the question of Tina-her identity, her power, and the role she ought to play in Asterleeds' future. In the wake of recent unrest,

her repeated acts of valor and unwavering defense of Asterleeds had not gone unnoticed.
A growing consensus emerged within the Council, advocating for her formal recognition as an asset rather than a liability. In response to these discussions, a proposal was introduced to officially acknowledge Tina's contributions and confer upon her the Hero Medal. Despite Commander Olvera's firm opposition-cautioning that thrusting Tina back into the public eye would only heighten the danger surrounding her-the proposal was approved.
However, the risks inherent in Tina's sensitive nature remain undeniable. Continued vigilance in both her protection and supervision is imperative.

50100001.Content: Olvera, do you still need help? I can help!

50100002.Content: No. It's far too dangerous here. Go and evacuate with the others.

50100003.Content: Since it's His Lordship's decision... I'll go assist with civilian evacuation. Forgive me, Tina, the ceremony will have to wait.

50100004.Content: But-are you asking me to run away? I'm not leaving until every last person is safe!

50100005.Content: No, Tina, I need to get you out-now.

50100006.Content: Everyone! Stay calm and follow the Corps' orders! Evacuate in an orderly fashion!

50100101.Content: Is it really that dangerous here?!

50100102.Content: What's going on?! They're evacuating the area. It's so scary...

50100103.Content: Aww, I didn't even get to see the ceremony...

50100104.Content: Alack... better just listen to the Commander...

50100106.Content: Welp, that was a wasted trip... Might as well head home.

50100107.Content: The Dominion clearing the square without even an explanation... strange.

50100202.Content: What a beautiful day-the sea breeze really is a blessing!

50100203.Content: I've been looking forward to the Council Chair's speech...

50100204.Content: When will Lady Tina come out? I brought flowers just for her!

50100206.Content: May the sea breeze protect Asterleeds.

50100207.Content: I really want to touch that medal-it's so shiny!

50100208.Content: Go, Little hero! We'll always cheer for you!

50110001.Content: All Asterleeds Defense Corps soldiers, prepare to clear the Void Engram and protect the people!

50110003.Content: Mr. Council Chair, we must get you to safety!

50110004.Content: No. I won't run-not while others are still in danger.

50110006.Content: Save your breath-I'm not so fragile. Asterleeds has no place for timid leaders!

50110009.Content: Get the wounded to the safe zone!

50110011.Content: Area secure! Use your extra skills to rally the crowd and speed up evacuation!

50110013.Content: I was startled! That was scary...

50120001.Content: Hey! Careful with those, they aren't yours to break!

50120002.Content: "My friend, do you remember the 'drink' I told you about? I still can't forget its taste. When we meet again, let's share another. It's the drink of true <style="emph-gn">iron-willed men</style>. Willed. Men, mark my words! Its color burns like fire. Ah... Drink deep, and let it set both heart and soul <style="emph-gn">ablaze</style>!"

50120011.Content: Is that really all you've got? I told you, you don't understand a thing. Now get out of my way!

50120012.Content: Heh... You're persistent. I wonder how you'll react when you find out what they did to Tina...

50120013.Content: Alright, this must be the package for Bertram. Now... time to figure out how to take him down. If I can just circle around to his back...

60070001.Content:
[Minsterhorn Village Bulletin]
A must-read for anyone entering the village:
1. All outsiders coming for business or a tour must follow the village's trade rules. Do not disturb village life.
2. The wheat fields are of great importance to the village. Anyone caught picking or polluting them will be permanently banned from entering the village.
3. Lastly, we welcome all friendly travelers to experience the culture and charm of Minsterhorn!
Chief Abel
...
[Brief History of Minsterhorn Village]
The Minsterhorn you see today is not the original location. The former village was destroyed in the war, but the survivors were temporarily sheltered by the main city of Asterleeds, and the village was able to continue.
After the war, the survivors, led by Chief Abel, rebuilt the current Minsterhorn Village here.

60070002.Content:
[Andra Resting Post]
Built beside the historic Andra Basin battlefield, this resting post was initially built by scavengers around the Andra Landing Battlefield after the war.
Later, due to malicious competition and resource snatching among the scavengers, it was taken over by two sisters: Cove and Liv.
There are many versions of how exactly they managed it. All that's known is, after that, the scavengers became wary of the two sisters, and the elder sister, Cove, became the resting post's overseer.
Eventually, it evolved into a resting place that provides lodging and meals for traveling merchants.
...
[Survival Rules of the Andra Resting Post]
1. If you see Cove frowning, leave the resting post immediately.
2. There are no cats in the resting post. If you see one, leave at once and inform Liv.
3. Do not easily trust anyone, especially those who smile.
4. Never scavenge the Andra ruins at night.
5. Whatever someone gives you, you must return something of equal value.

60070003.Content:
The chosen site for Kanamia originally featured a solitary boulder within a natural spring.
Upon arrival, the site selection scholars reported experiencing profound tranquility and spiritual clarity. This phenomenon was brought to the attention of Chief Rotroani.
Following approval, master stonemasons of Kanamia were commissioned to construct a commemorative statue titled "Ancestors and Their People," symbolizing the enduring protection of the ancestors over the people of Kanamia.
Subsequent investigations revealed that the spring's soothing effects stem from its subterranean connection to the sacred groundwater of the Forbidden Zone.
This water is believed to be imbued with the spiritual essence of the Ancestral Relic.
To the Kanamians, this was the protective force of their ancestors watching over them.

60070004.Content:
In Kanamian tradition, residents construct stone towers-known as "requiem towers"-by stacking stones in memory of deceased clan members.
According to legend, the taller the tower, the quicker the soul's journey to reunite with the ancestors.

Due to access restrictions around the Forbidden Zone, the Zeroing Spring has become the primary site for mourning, making wishes, and brooding over memories.

It is widely regarded as the second holiest location in Kanamia.

Locals often inscribe the names of lost loved ones on stones and cast them into the spring or construct requiem towers nearby.

Perhaps the prayers offered here may guide the beloved departed-those loved and lost-safely into the embrace of their ancestors, sparing their souls from an eternity of lonely wandering in this world...

60070005.Content:
A tree species unique to the Kanamia region. It has existed for centuries, even before the new Kanamia settlement was built.
Nourished by underground water influenced by ancestral relics, these trees continue to grow until the very moment of their decline. Even now, as Kanamia has built treehouses around them, the immortal trees keep growing taller and larger.

There's a saying passed down in Kanamia: the immortal trees can form a spiritual bond with certain special individuals.
Once in resonance, one can "communicate" with the tree and even guide its growth.
But no one has ever succeeded. It remains only a legend.

60070006.Content:
1. Every member of the community must hold no belief that contradicts the teachings of the ancestors, honoring their wisdom above all.
2. The will of the ancestors must be upheld with the utmost respect. Every member of the community is bound to honor their sacred directives.
3. All living beings and the natural world must be treated with compassion and care. Cruelty towards them is strictly prohibited.
4. A filial duty to one's parents is paramount. Abandonment or disrespect towards them is forbidden.
5. Every member must not harm the lives or possessions of others.
6. Falsehoods, including slander and deceit, are forbidden.
7. The seizing of others' property or persons is prohibited.

60070007.Content:
A hundred years ago, the ancestors of the Kanamian were still scattered across the plains in small tribes, living off basic hunting and gathering.
Later, under the leadership of Rotroani's grandfather, Kanamia was unified. All the small tribes gathered together and gradually formed what is now the Kanamia Tribe.
The former practices of communal living, hunting, and gathering were preserved and evolved into today's extended-family model, hunting competitions, and a hybrid system of foraging and cultivation.
Over time, Kanamia also developed animal husbandry, aquaculture, infrastructure, and manufacturing techniques. People's daily lives became more structured, and the tribe's systems more complete.
Throughout this development, one thing has never changed: the Kanamia people's reverence for their ancestors.
To outsiders, this might seem like ignorance, but for the Kanamian, it is an unshakable foundation.
It is the ancestors who constantly remind every Kanamian that, no matter how history moves forward, one must always preserve sincerity, kindness, and a sense of awe toward the continent, nature, and the world.

60070008.Content:
The dwelling shared by Rorola and Rotroani, constructed in accordance with the traditional Kanamian practice of communal living. It also serves as a resting place for the village elders.
Within it remain numerous belongings from Rorola's early childhood, yet there is a conspicuous absence of personal artifacts from her adolescence or present life. She and her father used to leave notes for each other, but six years ago, their exchanges seemed to have stopped.
It's as if time in this treehouse has been frozen in the past.

60070009.Content:
At present, the treehouse bears numerous signs of recent activity.
Rorola and Rotroani have resumed their habit of exchanging daily notes-brief reminders concerning tribal matters or simple essentials like food, clothing, and shelter.
Beside Rorola's bed lies a growing collection of small treasures she has gathered-delicate flowers, beautiful stones, and other keepsakes.
Though I haven't witnessed their life here firsthand, traces of their presence are woven into every corner of the treehouse.

60080005.Content:
An Alternative Perspective on the Peace Treaty

In Year 602, Alician calendar, Byrnhald and Asterleeds signed the Peace Treaty.
From then on, Asterleeds gained its freedom.

But... are we truly free?
How many people have actually read the "Peace Treaty" carefully?
Here are a few clauses:
"From the date of signing this treaty, Asterleeds and Byrnhald shall maintain trade. Tax adjustments shall be made on a 6-month cycle, with changes not exceeding 0.5% per period. "
"From the date of signing this treaty, Asterleeds Defense Corps must lose at least 65% of its wartime establishment and shall not expand its establishment without authorization. "
"From the date of signing this treaty, Byrnhalds shall retain free access to Asterleeds. Asterleeds shall not refuse for any reason. "
...
Can you sense the arrogance hidden within these clauses?

Asterleeds has always regarded itself as the victor.
But when the treaty was signed, it did not hold a position of advantage.

Let's summarize:
First, according to reports from the various military squads, Byrnhald's main forces were largely intact at the time of the agreement.
Second, the war ended amidst the mysterious "Revelation" event, and Byrnhald never formally surrendered.
Lastly, the treaty contains no clauses clearly favoring the interests of Asterleeds.

Based on this solid evidence, we can make a bold conjecture:
The "Peace Treaty" is actually just a whitewash for a compromise.

Now let's analyze the post-war economy and politics:
...

60080009.Content:
Asterleeds' prosperity has long flowed with the tides of trade,
its strong shipbuilding tradition and Seaside advantage
ensuring its success in maritime commerce.

-The Primordial Engine,
retrofitted by Artisan Johnson,
became the first Legacy ever adapted as a ship engine,
Pioneering the integration of Legacy-powered propulsion with marine vessels.
Its successful use in propelling a small fishing boat
marked the dawn of Asterleeds' legendary maritime fishing era.

-The Second-Generation Engine,
designed by Chief Artisan Benedict and
retrofitted through the collaboration of elite craftsmen,
led to the discovery of an alternative Legacy known as the "Elite Engine."
With abundant Legacy reserves enabling mass production,
this technological advancement allowed Asterleeds to
dominate fisheries through naval superiority, ultimately laying the foundation for its maritime trade supremacy.

-The Third-Generation Engine,
enhanced by Chief Artisan Ted using the "Engram Engine" as its foundation,
unlocked the Legacy's full potential through precision modifications. With its increased output
enabling the propulsion of giant oceanic cargo vessels,

this breakthrough catalyzed a new epoch in Asterleeds' maritime shipping industry.

60080010.Content:
Following the conclusion of the Asterleeds Independence War, the Council implemented several groundbreaking measures, including government transparency, freedom of speech, and the promotion of cultural diversity.
Their vision was to mold Asterleeds into a city of complete freedom.
...
One noteworthy decision was to keep the Council Hall open to the public around the clock.
This is a bold move,
which sparked immediate controversy,
with critics accusing it of being nothing more than a publicity stunt, overly dramatized for effect.
...
Yet, without question, whenever Asterleeds is mentioned, the word "freedom" is never far behind.
Whether mocked or admired, the open Council Hall has become synonymous with the city itself.
In this regard, the symbolism is the most important.
It represents Asterleeds' unwavering commitment to the ideals of liberty.

60080011.Content:
In summary,
long-standing dissatisfaction had been brewing within Asterleeds regarding the policies imposed by Byrnhald.
The eventual uprising was merely a matter of time.

In the 600th year of the Alician calendar, tensions escalated dramatically when Byrnhald imposed an excessively burdensome tax increase.
This policy resulted in a severe inflation of commodity prices in Asterleeds-
so extreme that a single piece of cake cost approximately 200 Lunos, equivalent to the wages of a laborer over ten days.
This economic pressure served as the immediate catalyst for the Asterleeds Independence War.

-The Andra Basin Skirmish- The First Spark That Shattered Chains
Following the outbreak of Asterleeds Independence War,
Byrnhald deployed its vanguard forces-including the Dark Mist Legion-via maritime entry into the Andra Basin.
There, they encountered the Asterleeds Defense Corps soldiers led by Commander Olvera. A significant engagement ensued, now referred to as the Defense Battle of Andra Basin.
During this operation, Olvera and a rising figure, Tina, cooperated strategically to repel the invading force.
After the war, Tina was requested by Olvera to become her aide-de-camp.

60080012.Content:
When war truly breaks out, ideals alone can't solve everything.
Against a nation like Byrnhald, Asterleeds was severely disadvantaged.
At the start of the war, Asterleeds' equipment was very outdated,
while Byrnhald's technology was far more advanced.
Once the fighting began, the Asterleeds Defense Corps were mocked by Byrnhald for their outdated gear.


So how did Asterleeds turn the tables around? Where was its path forward?
This brings us to Asterleeds' legendary figures-Olvera and Tina.
During the Asterleeds Independence War, Olvera served as the commander of the Defense Corps, with Tina as her deputy.
The forces they led could always turn the tide under dire circumstances and win against the odds.
- The early ambush on the plains on 601
- Kanamia Forest Skirmish
...
More importantly, their feats quickly spread among the Defense Corps. Wherever they went, they never lost.
This also became a sort of psychological warfare for the under-equipped and outnumbered Defense Corps: if you can't win with numbers or gear, then win with morale.

Additionally, some councilors and artisans had long anticipated a war with Byrnhald.
They secretly invested heavily in the Artisan Guild to develop prototype equipment.
Thanks to the inspiration of figures like Olvera and Tina,
along with many other factors, the gap between Asterleeds and Byrnhald slowly closed.

60080013.Content:
Back then, living conditions were harsh, and there weren't so many Legacies that had been excavated.
Legacies related to housing, furniture, and home improvement were especially scarce.
According to some elders, Asterleeds at that time could barely be called a city, it was more like a town in scale.
As the population grew rapidly, issues like housing shortages, insufficient basic goods, and poor infrastructure emerged.
The then-government-what would later become the Council-issued public calls for construction artisans, but very few responded.

Under such circumstances, a group of artisans stepped forward, willing to put aside their valuable Legacy research and
devote themselves to the hard work of designing housing, restoring city infrastructure, and crafting furniture.

You must understand: engaging with and researching Legacies is what motivates many to become artisans. It's their dream.
These artisans knew full well that the reconstruction of Asterleeds would take years.
This meant they would no longer have the time or opportunity to work with Legacies, and their early research would be lost to time.
...

The lead artisan was Webb.
Although Legacy usage was not widespread at the time, he was determined to design an energy network system for the city.

This was an extremely bold and forward-thinking concept. It's thanks to his early planning that energy integration was possible during the initial construction phase.
This laid the foundation for modern Asterleeds' Legacy

60080015.Content:
As the Asterleeds Independence War stretched beyond its first grueling year, the once-unshakable front of Byrnhald began to fracture. Whispers of internal discord rippled through their ranks, and the effects were soon felt on the battlefield-
supply lines faltered for reasons that remained unclear.
Consequently, the fighting force was severely weakened.
In contrast, Asterleeds-
with the support of skilled artisans-upgraded its military equipment, achieving outstanding results in holding back the enemy.
The people of Asterleeds' fervent longing for freedom has not been dimmed by sacrifice.
Inspired by Olvera and Tina, numerous heroes emerged among the Asterleeds Defense Corps, whose courage continued to grow.

In the first year of the Asterleeds Independence War, Byrnhald failed to defeat Asterleeds.
...
As the war entered its second year,
Byrnhald's cross-regional operations drained substantial resources, and even the
once-invincible Byrnhald Knights began to show signs of fatigue.

Despite these challenges, Byrnhald refused to withdraw its troops, leading the war into a prolonged battle of attrition.
With the advantage of fighting on home turf, Asterleeds gradually gained the upper hand in the struggle.

Just as the situation was becoming clearer, an unexpected piece of news arrived...

60080016.Content:
-Asterleeds Independence War IV-
At the end of the Asterleeds Independence War, the Creed abruptly issued a warning to both warring sides: The Seal of Hruga,
located at the center of the sea, had been broken, unleashing a catastrophic outbreak of Void Engram in the surrounding regions.
All living beings consumed by the it were transformed into mindless monsters...
If the The Seal of Hruga not restored in time, the disaster threatened not only humanity but the entire Continent of Magna.

Unexpectedly, this sudden calamity led to an unprecedented unification of human forces.
Under the directive of the Creed, not only Asterleeds and Byrnhald, but also adventurers from across the lands-
and even nomadic tribes-joined together in the fight against the Void Engram.

For a time, humanity surged with collective resolve, shining like stars against the darkness.
Their fervent efforts even drew the attention of the Divine. The Bapharian Divines responded by sending messengers to aid humanity in overcoming the crisis.

After enduring great hardship, the allied forces triumphed.
The conspiracy of the Hruga Believers was thwarted, and the The Seal of Hruga was successfully restored.

Following this victory, Byrnhald and Asterleeds finally
signed a ceasefire-the Peace Treaty-under the mediation of the Creed.

From that moment on, the people of Asterleeds stepped into a new era of freedom.

60080017.Content:

60080201.Content:
(This is a neatly written letter radiating sunlight.)
Dear Federico,
I am so happy to see you pursuing your dream (of course, I'm also a little sad that my lovely little son has left my side), but I know you are so smart and will surely achieve great things. This village of ours is too small to fulfill your ambitions.
The day you came back covered in wounds after bravely fighting to protect an old man who was being robbed,
you don't know how sad I was, how many tears I shed, my dear Federico...
Many neighbors and young people on the street mocked your weakness, but I know, only your mother knows, that it is all because of your kind virtues.
Believe firmly that your virtues are more powerful than your fists, Federico. Do not forget this. I hope you are doing well in Asterleeds!
P.S.: Is it cold? Are you eating well? Have you made any new friends? Is your living allowance still enough?
If you run into any trouble, remember to write back!

60080202.Content:
(This letter is written in slightly messy handwriting, clearly reflecting the writer's lively personality.) My dear brother! I'm so happy you've decided to chase your dream-and you really did it!
An adventurer! And in Asterleeds, no less!
What an incredible place it is. Everything and everyone there seems to be made of dreams and sunshine. The sea sparkles, the economy thrives, and the commercial capital is not only a center of trade, but also a city of art, of freedom, and of miracles. It holds a long history filled with legends, and yet it keeps evolving and moving forward.
In my imagination, it's as sweet and beautiful as a glass candy wrapper.
As for you-I'm not worried one bit, dear Federico. You're so clever, and you always understand how others feel. You just need a little experience, and you'll grow up faster than anyone else.
I truly believe you'll become a great adventurer! (But hey-if you ever run into anything upsetting, just write to me! I won't tell Mom, promise, heh)
Also! If you ever meet the legendary Airona, please, please get her autograph! And if you can, could you ask her whether the details about the The Seal of HrugaWar in her latest book, The Legend of the Eternal Earth, are actually true?
It's almost dawn here, so I'll stop writing now.
Your sister, who's eagerly waiting for your reply and really hates making breakfast,
-Anna

60080203.Content:
(This is a draft of a letter from a young adventurer to his family. Below is a collection of discarded drafts.)
To my dearest mother,
I've been in Asterleeds for over a month now, and just recently, I passed the entrance exam for the Pioneer Bureau-I'm officially an adventurer! I'm so happy. All the effort I put in has finally paid off.
(This sentence is crossed out.) At first, the exam was quite challenging for me, until I realized that brute strength wasn't everything for beating the monsters. Mastering the use of Legacy weapons turned out to be just as important-and that became the key to victory.
As a novice adventurer, the Pioneer Bureau introduced me to a senior mentor. It wasn't mandatory-more like a friendly guide to chat with and share life experiences. Luckily, we get along really well. He's cheerful, warm, and incredibly familiar with Asterleeds. He's shown me so much about the city, and it feels like we're more friends than mentor and apprentice. It's been great.
Speaking of Asterleeds-the sunshine here is wonderful, the city is lively, and there are so many more people than back home. The streets are always bustling with travelers and locals from all walks of life. (This sentence is crossed out.) I've been eating really well lately-there's so much going on that my appetite has grown. You probably wouldn't recognize me if you saw me now. I've gotten a lot stronger!
But I must confess-no delicacy here rivals your cooking, Mother. I already crave that taste of your tomato & braised lamb stew (the next few words blur into ink-smudged stains... This draft ends here.)
60080203.ChatName: Draft of a Reply to Mom

60080204.Content:
(This is a draft of a letter from a young adventurer to his family, with many crossed-out sections and scribbled notes.)
To Anna,
(This entire paragraph is crossed out.) I have to be honest. I do like Asterleeds, but that doesn't stop me from sometimes feeling like I don't belong here. In this colorful, bright, steaming, shining city, there is everything-silks, saddles, belts, dashing hats, beautiful feathers, satin, weapons, Legacy items, jewelry-everything the world has to offer, gathered here and within reach. I enjoy admiring it all, yet still... sometimes, I feel out of place. This city feels like a stationary ship, and many who come here chasing their dreams don't realize that their tickets have an expiration date. I'm chasing mine too, but I often worry-what if all my efforts end up meaningless?
(There is a scribbled note at the top of the next paragraph: "Use this paragraph!")
Anna, listen-I'm doing well, and I'm definitely not going to give you a reason to laugh at me! Don't worry, if anything goes wrong, I'll figure it out. Don't forget, I used to help you out at school when we were kids-though, yeah, I'll admit I also kept you up way too late chatting.
I've actually seen Airona a few times... but I haven't had the courage to talk to her yet. She's Airona, after all-and I'm still just a beginner out here. (The letter pauses here, unfinished.)
60080204.ChatName: Draft of a Reply to Anna

60080206.Content:
Welcome to your stay at The Double-Faced Coin! Please read and follow the guidelines below-unless you'd like to see your bill grow longer than your adventure log.
1. The Double-Faced Coin is an tavern that welcomes adventurers and travelers from all corners of the world. Our prices are low to make your stay affordable, but we ask all guests to uphold a sense of community. Please maintain personal hygiene, respect others' customs and space, and refrain from scribbling on walls or furniture.
2. The second floor houses shared group accommodations. Bedding is available in the storage room beneath the stairs. Note: high bunk beds require an additional fee. For laundry services, please contact Miss Madeline (the name has been crossed out. Note: resigned) Sabrina from Bluesea Laundry, who makes daily visits.
3. Personal lockers with locks are available in the accommodation rooms. Keep your keys and belongings secure. Acts of theft, racketeering, quarrels, or other misconduct are strictly prohibited.
4. Books placed in the accommodation rooms are part of our shared library. Feel free to read and enjoy them! Guests are encouraged to contribute their own books to enrich the collection-or head downstairs, order a Drink Mixing, and join a good conversation on books. Let stories and knowledge flow freely.
5. You bet! We also welcome you to share your tales with fellow travelers you meet by chance!
60080206.ChatName: The Double-Faced Coin Guidelines- For Guests

60080207.Content:
Everyone, welcome to The Double-Faced Coin-where laughter, flavors, and tales intertwine.
The theme of The Double-Faced Coin is human connection-our hall offers shelter to all loneliness, celebrates every encounter, and lets the curling aroma of good food and drink swirl among the clinking of glasses.
So the Tavernmaster has set up this Message Board. Feel free to leave a note, share a tale, or even add your own "Hall Rules" to help keep the magic alive.
1. Outside the realm of stories, all acts that go against common decency, social norms, or the laws of the land are forbidden inside The Double-Faced Coin. Also-no bickering.
2. Please show respect to our staff and other guests. If you're in trouble or need assistance, just ask.
3. Pets are welcome-but only the polite ones, please make sure they don't negatively affect the experience of other guests.
...
76. If you stumble upon any mysterious puzzles or treasure hunter clues, be sure to verify if they're real first!
...
94. It is strictly forbidden to place julienned potatoes and shredded ginger on the same plate.
...
209. Respect the tavern's music. No skipping tracks. No disc-swapping chaos.
Amendment 209: And don't even think about bumping your song to the top of the playlist!!!
...
334. The Double-Faced Coin encourages spirited dancing. But please, not on the tables. And if you're a couple? Keep your waltzing at least one meter away from any single stranger. It's just... not a great idea.

60080611.Content:
Author: Jon

In the past, conditions were extremely harsh, and the level of Legacy excavation was nowhere near what it is today.
Legacies beneficial to housing, furniture, or domestic life were exceedingly rare.
According to some older residents, Asterleeds at that time could hardly even be called a city-more like a small town in scale.
With a rapidly growing population, residents were soon faced with issues like housing shortages, lack of daily necessities, and inadequate public infrastructure.
The then-governing body, which would later evolve into the Council, issued a call for housing artisans. But few responded.

Under such circumstances, a number of Legacy experts stepped forward. They willingly put aside their valuable research work,
and threw themselves into grueling tasks like house design, infrastructure repair, and furniture crafting.

One must understand-working with Legacies is the very reason many became artisans. It was their dream.
These Legacy experts knew full well that Asterleeds restoration would take many years.
Which meant... they would no longer have the chance to frequently interact with Legacies. All their early research would be reduced to nothing.
Even so, this group of artisans used their knowledge of Legacy
and combined it with traditional construction techniques-they created something unprecedented.
...
The leading artisan among them was named "Webber."
At a time when Legacy utilization was still low, he insisted on designing a city-wide energy network system.

This idea was both bold and visionary. Thanks to his early planning during the reconstruction phase,
Asterleeds today enjoys the widespread use of Legacy-based energy systems. His contributions laid the foundation.
In today's Asterleeds, kitchen appliances in wealthy households, ventilation systems in restaurants...
or even lighting, signage systems, etc.-all operate thanks to the energy network designed by Webber.

To commemorate the dedication of these artisans, and Webber's foresight,
Asterleeds energy system was officially renamed "Webber."
These admirable artisans.

60080612.Content:
-Technology Advances with Every Discovery-
Author: Mason Stonecutter
-A Promising Future
Recently, some argue that technological development is overly dependent on Legacies.
This is a narrow-minded view.
Artisans shouldn't only focus on the technology in their hands. They need to understand the real value of Legacy research.
...
The Creed restricts access to high-risk Legacies.
But it does not hinder the Legacy research.
On the contrary, there has been an undeniable surge in innovations emerging from Legacy studies.

Some might say that the artisans' brilliant achievements are just a byproduct of adventurers discovering Legacies.
But I believe the value of Legacy research isn't limited to the act of study itself.

As the saying goes, "A rising tide lifts all boats." The immense power of Legacies does not merely pull artisans along.
It drives us forward.

If those people set aside their bias and look at the Artisan Guild as a whole, they would see:
Thanks to the impressive progress in Legacy modifications,
innovations have emerged across other fields as well, and the research within the Guild has been elevated overall.
...

With the continued efforts of adventurers, perhaps more Legacies will be discovered, or perhaps not.
Either way, Legacy research has opened a small window,
through which we can see a future filled with infinite possibilities.

A future that belongs to us, to humanity itself.
And that future is being forged by the hands of artisans.

60080613.Content:
When you read this note, are you pacing back and forth?
Or wiping every table?
Opening and closing drawers? Searching for those nonexistent trinkets?
Thinking: "Maybe I should go downstairs and buy a bottle of coffee"?

Don't try to romanticize this behavior by calling it "seeking inspiration."
Artisan, this is not a good habit.

60080614.Content:
Among the many apartment buildings lining Asterleeds main street, there is one that stands out. Unlike the nearby residential blocks, this hive-like structure has been repurposed into a workspace for scholars. Researchers from all walks of life and from across the The Continent of Magna live and work here-learning, exchanging ideas with students, and cultivating a rich, dynamic academic atmosphere.
In a city where prices and rent continue to soar, the thirst for knowledge and energy for exploration inside this building has never waned. Perhaps this is the very spirit that fuels Asterleeds inquisitiveness. The hallways are lined with posters of various disciplines, seminars, research paper titles, and intricate diagrams. Debates often echo through the corridors-clashing tones and viewpoints from different academic schools fill the air.
Naturally, you'll see young students scattered across the city-troubled by academic dilemmas or confused about their future-they, too, have become part of Asterleeds vibrant and tangled cultural landscape.

60080615.Content:
Many of Asterleeds traditional street stalls-reflecting the cultural customs of this port-city of commerce-offer you salty smoked meats, flavorful seafood sauces, body-strengthening vegetables, rich fats, and fiery hotclouds of spice... but provide no seating. There's a kind of fleeting atmosphere here. People come to drink heartily, not to taste delicately.
Like the rolling sea, the city breathes in motion-it never lingers still. That is the air of Asterleeds. But then, as a visitor, how do you know which stall has the best flavor? There's one very simple trick: trust the kids on the street. The orphanages in Asterleeds take in children who lost their families to wilderness monsters or the Asterleeds Independence War. And in their eyes, you'll find the truest map of alleyways and taste.

60080616.Content:
Adventurers also tend to pick up the cooking style passed down from the harbor: Ingredients are few, prep is simple. Put plainly, it's all because the ingredients themselves are exceptional.
For grilled meat, the best wood is fine oak or olive wood. Seasoning? Just salt. Spices are great, yes, but for those in a rush to pursue dreams or trade opportunities, spice use already belongs to another, more leisurely kind of cooking.

60080617.Content: Ugly in appearance and notoriously difficult to cultivate, yet possessing a taste beyond words-this is the wild mountain mushroom. It's common knowledge around Asterleeds: to locate the best, freshest wild mushrooms, you need either a specially trained, sharp-nosed dog, or a specially trained, sharp-eyed adventurer. Just a touch of wild flavor from nature can completely transform a dish steeped in the city's scent. So, when harvest season comes-and if your budget allows-head over to the Pioneer Bureau and put in a commission. Try your luck and get some top-grade wild mushrooms.
60080617.ChatName: The Fun of Wild Mountain Mushrooms

60080618.Content: Before you decide to throw all your ingredients into the pot-stop and think for a moment! You know what happens when you swing a weapon at wood. You know a rock thrown from a height makes a splash. You know that when people are hurt, they bleed. So why don't you stop to think? Cooking isn't some miraculous act done without thought. It's an art built on solid logic. First-what's your main ingredient? What complementary ingredients will you use? What cooking method suits them best? Only when you've thought through all this-organized your ideas and prepped your tools-can things go smoothly.

60080619.Content:
Specialty Drinks Shop
We're devoted to the rich sediment and malty aroma born of traditional brewing,
enchanted by the diverse flavors revealed through unique barley varieties,
and captivated by the character each batch draws from the weather-and even the brewer's mood.
This is our passion. This is Asterleeds Traditional specialty drink.

That's not true!
Ha! Bet you didn't even realize we're called "Whim's End Tavern!"
I wrote that whole long paragraph just to show how good it feels to let loose after keeping things buttoned up!
Obviously, the most important thing about a drink is that it tastes good - so honestly, throw in whatever you want!
Our creed: whim rules, flavor reigns supreme!
(Clears throat) Loud, sure - but not quite in sync. One more time: Whim-rules, flavor-reigns-supreme!
Now that's what I'm talking about! Behold-the menu of the season!

60080623.Content:
Silver dances atop the waves
From the sky
Falls the heartbeat I gather

The starlight on her lashes falls
The tide brushes over our ankles
Smoothing away all unspoken words

Shells deep in the sand count the passing years
The moonlight writes our shadows into
Tonight's song

60080624.Content:
Newsflash: Fireworks Festival Restarts! Tina Returns Safely
By: A Spectacled Shrimp

3 days ago, there was an accident at the Fireworks Festival opening. During Tina's medal ceremony, a strange black mist suddenly appeared.
According to eyewitnesses, it resembled the terrifying Void Engram from years past.
Fortunately, the Asterleeds Defense Corps and the Pioneer Bureau quickly contained the scene and no one was injured.
What's strange is that Tina disappeared during the chaos. Though she has now returned safely, why did she disappear? Was the strange mist truly Void Engram? The mysteries surrounding the incident remain deeply intriguing.
The Council Hall has now issued a statement declaring the situation under control, and both the Seabreeze Festival and the Fireworks Festival will proceed as planned.
"We can't let this incident ruin everyone's good mood," said Council Chair Lamond. But is there a deeper meaning behind his words?
Our reporters will continue to follow this story.
